73 bool SemaSYCL::isSyclType(QualType Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::SYCLType TypeName) {
74  const auto *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
75  if (!RD)
76  return false;
77 
78  if (const auto *Attr = RD->getAttr<SYCLTypeAttr>())
79  return Attr->getType() == TypeName;
80 
81  if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
82  if (CXXRecordDecl *TemplateDecl =
83  CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate()->getTemplatedDecl())
84  if (const auto *Attr = TemplateDecl->getAttr<SYCLTypeAttr>())
85  return Attr->getType() == TypeName;
86 
87  return false;
88 }

90 static bool isSyclAccessorType(QualType Ty) {
91  return SemaSYCL::isSyclType(Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::accessor) ||
92  SemaSYCL::isSyclType(Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::local_accessor);
93 }

95 // FIXME: Accessor property lists should be modified to use compile-time
96 // properties. Once implemented, this function (and possibly all/most code
97 // in SemaSYCL.cpp handling no_alias and buffer_location property) can be
98 // removed.
99 static bool isAccessorPropertyType(QualType Ty,
100  SYCLTypeAttr::SYCLType TypeName) {
101  if (const auto *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
102  if (const auto *Parent = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD->getParent()))
103  if (const auto *Attr = Parent->getAttr<SYCLTypeAttr>())
104  return Attr->getType() == TypeName;
105 
106  return false;
107 }

113 ExprResult SemaSYCL::ActOnSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(ParsedType PT) {
114  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
115  QualType QT = Sema::GetTypeFromParser(PT, &TInfo);
116  assert(TInfo && "couldn't get type info from a type from the parser?");
117  SourceLocation TypeLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
118 
119  return BuildSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(TypeLoc, QT);
120 }

122 ExprResult SemaSYCL::BuildSYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
123  QualType SourceTy) {
124  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
125  if (SemaRef.RequireCompleteType(
126  Loc, SourceTy, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
127  /*__builtin_num_fields*/ 0))
128  return ExprError();
129 
130  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
131  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
132  << /*__builtin_num_fields*/ 0;
133  return ExprError();
134  }
135  }
136  return new (getASTContext())
137  SYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExpr(Loc, SourceTy, getASTContext().getSizeType());
138 }

143  assert(TInfo && "couldn't get type info from a type from the parser?");
144  SourceLocation TypeLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
145 
146  return BuildSYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(TypeLoc, QT, Idx);

148 
149 ExprResult SemaSYCL::BuildSYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
150  QualType SourceTy,
151  Expr *Idx) {
152  // If the expression appears in an evaluated context, we want to give an
153  // error so that users don't attempt to use the value of this expression.
154  if (!SemaRef.isUnevaluatedContext()) {
155  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_evaluated)
156  << /*__builtin_field_type*/ 0;
157  return ExprError();
158  }
159 
160  // We may not be able to calculate the field type (the source type may be a
161  // dependent type), so use the source type as a basic fallback. This will
162  // ensure that the AST node will have a dependent type that gets resolved
163  // later to the real type.
164  QualType FieldTy = SourceTy;
165  ExprValueKind ValueKind = VK_PRValue;
166  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
167  if (SemaRef.RequireCompleteType(
168  Loc, SourceTy, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
169  /*__builtin_field_type*/ 1))
170  return ExprError();
171 
172  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
173  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
174  << /*__builtin_field_type*/ 1;
175  return ExprError();
176  }
177 
178  if (!Idx->isValueDependent()) {
179  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxVal =
180  Idx->getIntegerConstantExpr(getASTContext());
181  if (IdxVal) {
182  RecordDecl *RD = SourceTy->getAsRecordDecl();
183  assert(RD && "Record type but no record decl?");
184  int64_t Index = IdxVal->getExtValue();
185 
186  if (Index < 0) {
187  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
188  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_nonnegative_index)
189  << /*fields*/ 0;
190  return ExprError();
191  }
192 
193  // Ensure that the index is within range.
194  int64_t NumFields = std::distance(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end());
195  if (Index >= NumFields) {
196  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
197  diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_index_out_of_range)
198  << toString(*IdxVal, 10) << SourceTy << /*fields*/ 0;
199  return ExprError();
200  }
201  const FieldDecl *FD = *std::next(RD->field_begin(), Index);
202  FieldTy = FD->getType();
203 
204  // If the field type was a reference type, adjust it now.
205  if (FieldTy->isLValueReferenceType()) {
206  ValueKind = VK_LValue;
207  FieldTy = FieldTy.getNonReferenceType();
208  } else if (FieldTy->isRValueReferenceType()) {
209  ValueKind = VK_XValue;
210  FieldTy = FieldTy.getNonReferenceType();
211  }
212  }
213  }
214  }
215  return new (getASTContext())
216  SYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Idx, FieldTy, ValueKind);
217 }

254 
255 ExprResult SemaSYCL::BuildSYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExpr(SourceLocation Loc,
256  QualType SourceTy,
257  Expr *Idx) {
258  // If the expression appears in an evaluated context, we want to give an
259  // error so that users don't attempt to use the value of this expression.
260  if (!SemaRef.isUnevaluatedContext()) {
261  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_evaluated)
262  << /*__builtin_base_type*/ 1;
263  return ExprError();
264  }
265 
266  // We may not be able to calculate the base type (the source type may be a
267  // dependent type), so use the source type as a basic fallback. This will
268  // ensure that the AST node will have a dependent type that gets resolved
269  // later to the real type.
270  QualType BaseTy = SourceTy;
271  if (!SourceTy->isDependentType()) {
272  if (SemaRef.RequireCompleteType(
273  Loc, SourceTy, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_complete_type,
274  /*__builtin_base_type*/ 3))
275  return ExprError();
276 
277  if (!SourceTy->isRecordType()) {
278  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_record_type)
279  << /*__builtin_base_type*/ 3;
280  return ExprError();
281  }
282 
283  if (!Idx->isValueDependent()) {
284  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxVal =
285  Idx->getIntegerConstantExpr(getASTContext());
286  if (IdxVal) {
287  CXXRecordDecl *RD = SourceTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
288  assert(RD && "Record type but no record decl?");
289  int64_t Index = IdxVal->getExtValue();
290 
291  if (Index < 0) {
292  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
293  diag::err_sycl_type_trait_requires_nonnegative_index)
294  << /*bases*/ 1;
295  return ExprError();
296  }
297 
298  // Ensure that the index is within range.
299  if (Index >= RD->getNumBases()) {
300  Diag(Idx->getExprLoc(),
301  diag::err_sycl_builtin_type_trait_index_out_of_range)
302  << toString(*IdxVal, 10) << SourceTy << /*bases*/ 1;
303  return ExprError();
304  }
305 
306  const CXXBaseSpecifier &Spec = *std::next(RD->bases_begin(), Index);
307  BaseTy = Spec.getType();
308  }
309  }
310  }
311  return new (getASTContext())
312  SYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExpr(Loc, SourceTy, Idx, BaseTy);
313 }

315 // This information is from Section 4.13 of the SYCL spec
316 // https://www.khronos.org/registry/SYCL/specs/sycl-1.2.1.pdf
317 // This function returns false if the math lib function
318 // corresponding to the input builtin is not supported
319 // for SYCL
320 static bool IsSyclMathFunc(unsigned BuiltinID) {
321  switch (BuiltinID) {
322  case Builtin::BIlround:
323  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lround:
324  case Builtin::BIceill:
325  case Builtin::BI__builtin_ceill:
326  case Builtin::BIcopysignl:
327  case Builtin::BI__builtin_copysignl:
328  case Builtin::BIcosl:
329  case Builtin::BI__builtin_cosl:
330  case Builtin::BIexpl:
331  case Builtin::BI__builtin_expl:
332  case Builtin::BIexp2l:
333  case Builtin::BI__builtin_exp2l:
334  case Builtin::BIfabsl:
335  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fabsl:
336  case Builtin::BIfloorl:
337  case Builtin::BI__builtin_floorl:
338  case Builtin::BIfmal:
339  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmal:
340  case Builtin::BIfmaxl:
341  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmaxl:
342  case Builtin::BIfminl:
343  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fminl:
344  case Builtin::BIfmodl:
345  case Builtin::BI__builtin_fmodl:
346  case Builtin::BIlogl:
347  case Builtin::BI__builtin_logl:
348  case Builtin::BIlog10l:
349  case Builtin::BI__builtin_log10l:
350  case Builtin::BIlog2l:
351  case Builtin::BI__builtin_log2l:
352  case Builtin::BIpowl:
353  case Builtin::BI__builtin_powl:
354  case Builtin::BIrintl:
355  case Builtin::BI__builtin_rintl:
356  case Builtin::BIroundl:
357  case Builtin::BI__builtin_roundl:
358  case Builtin::BIsinl:
359  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sinl:
360  case Builtin::BIsqrtl:
361  case Builtin::BI__builtin_sqrtl:
362  case Builtin::BItruncl:
363  case Builtin::BI__builtin_truncl:
364  case Builtin::BIlroundl:
365  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lroundl:
366  case Builtin::BIlroundf:
367  case Builtin::BI__builtin_lroundf:
368  return false;
369  default:
370  break;
371  }
372  return true;
373 }

375 bool SemaSYCL::isDeclAllowedInSYCLDeviceCode(const Decl *D) {
376  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
377  const IdentifierInfo *II = FD->getIdentifier();
378 
379  // Allow __builtin_assume_aligned and __builtin_printf to be called from
380  // within device code.
381  if (FD->getBuiltinID() &&
382  (FD->getBuiltinID() == Builtin::BI__builtin_assume_aligned ||
383  FD->getBuiltinID() == Builtin::BI__builtin_printf))
384  return true;
385 
386  // Allow to use `::printf` only for CUDA.
387  if (getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
388  if (FD->getBuiltinID() == Builtin::BIprintf)
389  return true;
390  }
391  const DeclContext *DC = FD->getDeclContext();
392  if (II && II->isStr("__spirv_ocl_printf") &&
393  !FD->isDefined() &&
394  FD->getLanguageLinkage() == CXXLanguageLinkage &&
395  DC->getEnclosingNamespaceContext()->isTranslationUnit())
396  return true;
397  }
398  return false;
399 }

404 static bool isZeroSizedArray(SemaSYCL &S, QualType Ty) {
405  if (const auto *CAT = S.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(Ty))
406  return CAT->isZeroSize();
407  return false;
408 }
409 
410 static void checkSYCLType(SemaSYCL &S, QualType Ty, SourceRange Loc,
411  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited,
412  SourceRange UsedAtLoc = SourceRange()) {
413  // Not all variable types are supported inside SYCL kernels,
414  // for example the quad type __float128 will cause errors in the
415  // SPIR-V translation phase.
416  // Here we check any potentially unsupported declaration and issue
417  // a deferred diagnostic, which will be emitted iff the declaration
418  // is discovered to reside in kernel code.
419  // The optional UsedAtLoc param is used when the SYCL usage is at a
420  // different location than the variable declaration and we need to
421  // inform the user of both, e.g. struct member usage vs declaration.
422 
423  bool Emitting = false;
424 
425  //--- check types ---
426 
427  // zero length arrays
428  if (isZeroSizedArray(S, Ty)) {
429  S.DiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size)
430  << 1;
431  Emitting = true;
432  }
433 
434  // variable length arrays
435  if (Ty->isVariableArrayType()) {
436  S.DiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_vla_unsupported) << 0;
437  Emitting = true;
438  }
439 
440  // Sub-reference array or pointer, then proceed with that type.
441  while (Ty->isAnyPointerType() || Ty->isArrayType())
442  Ty = QualType{Ty->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
443 
444  // __int128, __int128_t, __uint128_t, long double, __float128
445  if (Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Int128) ||
446  Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::UInt128) ||
447  Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongDouble) ||
448  Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::BFloat16) ||
449  (Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Float128) &&
450  !S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type())) {
451  S.DiagIfDeviceCode(Loc.getBegin(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
452  << Ty.getUnqualifiedType().getCanonicalType();
453  Emitting = true;
454  }
455 
456  if (Emitting && UsedAtLoc.isValid())
457  S.DiagIfDeviceCode(UsedAtLoc.getBegin(), diag::note_used_here);
458 
459  //--- now recurse ---
460  // Pointers complicate recursion. Add this type to Visited.
461  // If already there, bail out.
462  if (!Visited.insert(Ty).second)
463  return;
464 
465  if (const auto *ATy = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Ty))
466  return checkSYCLType(S, ATy->getModifiedType(), Loc, Visited);
467 
468  if (const auto *RD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl()) {
469  for (const auto &Field : RD->fields())
470  checkSYCLType(S, Field->getType(), Field->getSourceRange(), Visited, Loc);
471  } else if (const auto *FPTy = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Ty)) {
472  for (const auto &ParamTy : FPTy->param_types())
473  checkSYCLType(S, ParamTy, Loc, Visited);
474  checkSYCLType(S, FPTy->getReturnType(), Loc, Visited);
475  }
476 }
477 
478 void SemaSYCL::checkSYCLDeviceVarDecl(VarDecl *Var) {
479  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
480  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
481  QualType Ty = Var->getType();
482  SourceRange Loc = Var->getLocation();
483  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited;
484 
485  checkSYCLType(*this, Ty, Loc, Visited);
486 }

488 // Tests whether given function is a lambda function or '()' operator used as
489 // SYCL kernel body function (e.g. in parallel_for).
490 // NOTE: This is incomplete implemenation. See TODO in the FE TODO list for the
491 // ESIMD extension.
492 static bool isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(FunctionDecl *FD) {
493  return FD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call;
494 }
495 
496 static bool isSYCLUndefinedAllowed(const FunctionDecl *Callee,
497  const SourceManager &SrcMgr) {
498  if (!Callee)
499  return false;
500 
501  // The check below requires declaration name, make sure we have it.
502  if (!Callee->getIdentifier())
503  return false;
504 
505  // libstdc++-11 introduced an undefined function "void __failed_assertion()"
506  // which may lead to SemaSYCL check failure. However, this undefined function
507  // is used to trigger some compilation error when the check fails at compile
508  // time and will be ignored when the check succeeds. We allow calls to this
509  // function to support some important std functions in SYCL device.
510  return (Callee->getName() == LibstdcxxFailedAssertion) &&
511  Callee->getNumParams() == 0 && Callee->getReturnType()->isVoidType() &&
512  SrcMgr.isInSystemHeader(Callee->getLocation());
513 }

515 // Helper function to report conflicting function attributes.
516 // F - the function, A1 - function attribute, A2 - the attribute it conflicts
517 // with.
518 static void reportConflictingAttrs(SemaSYCL &S, FunctionDecl *F, const Attr *A1,
519  const Attr *A2) {
520  S.Diag(F->getLocation(), diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
521  S.Diag(A1->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
522  S.Diag(A2->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
523  F->setInvalidDecl();
524 }

526 /// Returns the signed constant integer value represented by given expression
527 static int64_t getIntExprValue(const Expr *E, ASTContext &Ctx) {
528  return E->getIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx)->getSExtValue();
529 }

531 // Collect function attributes related to SYCL.
532 static void collectSYCLAttributes(SemaSYCL &S, FunctionDecl *FD,
533  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Attr *> &Attrs,
534  bool DirectlyCalled) {
535  if (!FD->hasAttrs())
536  return;
537 
538  // In SYCL 1.2.1 mode, the attributes are propagated from the function they
539  // are applied to onto the kernel which calls the function.
540  // In SYCL 2020 mode, the attributes are not propagated to the kernel.
541  if (DirectlyCalled || S.getASTContext().getLangOpts().getSYCLVersion() <
542  LangOptions::SYCL_2020) {
543  llvm::copy_if(FD->getAttrs(), std::back_inserter(Attrs), [](Attr *A) {
544  // FIXME: Make this list self-adapt as new SYCL attributes are added.
545  return isa<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr, IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr,
546  SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr,
547  SYCLIntelKernelArgsRestrictAttr, SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr,
548  SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhzAttr,
549  SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr, SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr,
550  SYCLIntelMinWorkGroupsPerComputeUnitAttr,
551  SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupsPerMultiprocessorAttr,
552  SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr, SYCLSimdAttr>(A);
553  });
554  }
555 
556  // Attributes that should not be propagated from device functions to a kernel.
557  if (DirectlyCalled) {
558  llvm::copy_if(FD->getAttrs(), std::back_inserter(Attrs), [](Attr *A) {
559  return isa<SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr, SYCLIntelMaxConcurrencyAttr,
560  SYCLIntelDisableLoopPipeliningAttr,
561  SYCLIntelInitiationIntervalAttr,
562  SYCLIntelUseStallEnableClustersAttr, SYCLDeviceHasAttr,
563  SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>(A);
564  });
565  }
566 }

568 class DiagDeviceFunction : public RecursiveASTVisitor<DiagDeviceFunction> {
569  SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef;
570  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &RecursiveFuncs;
571 
572 public:
573  DiagDeviceFunction(
574  SemaSYCL &S,
575  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &RecursiveFuncs)
576  : RecursiveASTVisitor(), SemaSYCLRef(S), RecursiveFuncs(RecursiveFuncs) {}
577 
578  void CheckBody(Stmt *ToBeDiagnosed) { TraverseStmt(ToBeDiagnosed); }
579 
580  bool VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *e) {
581  if (FunctionDecl *Callee = e->getDirectCallee()) {
582  Callee = Callee->getCanonicalDecl();
583  assert(Callee && "Device function canonical decl must be available");
584 
585  // Remember that all SYCL kernel functions have deferred
586  // instantiation as template functions. It means that
587  // all functions used by kernel have already been parsed and have
588  // definitions.
589  if (RecursiveFuncs.count(Callee)) {
590  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
591  << SemaSYCL::KernelCallRecursiveFunction;
592  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(Callee->getSourceRange().getBegin(),
593  diag::note_sycl_recursive_function_declared_here)
594  << SemaSYCL::KernelCallRecursiveFunction;
595  }
596 
597  if (const CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Callee))
598  if (Method->isVirtual() &&
599  !SemaSYCLRef.getLangOpts().SYCLAllowVirtualFunctions)
600  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
601  << SemaSYCL::KernelCallVirtualFunction;
602 
603  if (auto const *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Callee)) {
604  // FIXME: We need check all target specified attributes for error if
605  // that function with attribute can not be called from sycl kernel. The
606  // info is in ParsedAttr. We don't have to map from Attr to ParsedAttr
607  // currently. Erich is currently working on that in LLVM, once that is
608  // committed we need to change this".
609  if (FD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
610  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
611  << SemaSYCL::KernelCallDllimportFunction;
612  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::note_callee_decl) << FD;
613  }
614  }
615  // Specifically check if the math library function corresponding to this
616  // builtin is supported for SYCL
617  unsigned BuiltinID = Callee->getBuiltinID();
618  if (BuiltinID && !IsSyclMathFunc(BuiltinID)) {
619  StringRef Name =
620  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinID);
621  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_builtin_target_unsupported)
622  << Name << "SYCL device";
623  }
624  } else if (!SemaSYCLRef.getLangOpts().SYCLAllowFuncPtr &&
625  !e->isTypeDependent() &&
626  !isa<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(e->getCallee())) {
627  bool MaybeConstantExpr = false;
628  Expr *NonDirectCallee = e->getCallee();
629  if (!NonDirectCallee->isValueDependent())
630  MaybeConstantExpr =
631  NonDirectCallee->isCXX11ConstantExpr(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext());
632  if (!MaybeConstantExpr)
633  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(e->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
634  << SemaSYCL::KernelCallFunctionPointer;
635  }
636  return true;
637  }
638 
639  bool VisitCXXTypeidExpr(CXXTypeidExpr *E) {
640  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
641  << SemaSYCL::KernelRTTI;
642  return true;
643  }
644 
645  bool VisitCXXDynamicCastExpr(const CXXDynamicCastExpr *E) {
646  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_restrict)
647  << SemaSYCL::KernelRTTI;
648  return true;
649  }
650 
651  // Skip checking rules on variables initialized during constant evaluation.
652  bool TraverseVarDecl(VarDecl *VD) {
653  if (VD->isConstexpr())
654  return true;
655  return RecursiveASTVisitor::TraverseVarDecl(VD);
656  }
657 
658  // Skip checking rules on template arguments, since these are constant
659  // expressions.
660  bool TraverseTemplateArgumentLoc(const TemplateArgumentLoc &ArgLoc) {
661  return true;
662  }
663 
664  // Skip checking the static assert, both components are required to be
665  // constant expressions.
666  bool TraverseStaticAssertDecl(StaticAssertDecl *D) { return true; }
667 
668  // Make sure we skip the condition of the case, since that is a constant
669  // expression.
670  bool TraverseCaseStmt(CaseStmt *S) {
671  return TraverseStmt(S->getSubStmt());
672  }
673 
674  // Skip checking the size expr, since a constant array type loc's size expr is
675  // a constant expression.
676  bool TraverseConstantArrayTypeLoc(const ConstantArrayTypeLoc &ArrLoc) {
677  return true;
678  }
679 
680  bool TraverseIfStmt(IfStmt *S) {
681  if (std::optional<Stmt *> ActiveStmt =
682  S->getNondiscardedCase(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext())) {
683  if (*ActiveStmt)
684  return TraverseStmt(*ActiveStmt);
685  return true;
686  }
687  return RecursiveASTVisitor::TraverseIfStmt(S);
688  }
689 };
690 
691 // This type manages the list of device functions and recursive functions, as
692 // well as an entry point for attribute collection, for the translation unit
693 // during MarkDevices. On construction, this type makes sure that all of the
694 // root-device functions, (that is, those marked with SYCL_EXTERNAL) are
695 // collected. On destruction, it manages and runs the diagnostics required.
696 // When processing individual kernel/external functions, the
697 // SingleDeviceFunctionTracker type updates this type.
698 class DeviceFunctionTracker {
699  friend class SingleDeviceFunctionTracker;
700  CallGraph CG;
701  SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef;
702  // The list of functions used on the device, kept so we can diagnose on them
703  // later.
704  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> DeviceFunctions;
705  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const FunctionDecl *, 16> RecursiveFunctions;
706 
707  void CollectSyclExternalFuncs() {
708  for (CallGraphNode::CallRecord Record : CG.getRoot()->callees())
709  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Record.Callee->getDecl()))
710  if (FD->hasBody() && FD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
711  SemaSYCLRef.addSyclDeviceDecl(FD);
712  }
713 
714  CallGraphNode *getNodeForKernel(FunctionDecl *Kernel) {
715  assert(CG.getNode(Kernel) && "No call graph entry for a kernel?");
716  return CG.getNode(Kernel);
717  }
718 
719  void AddSingleFunction(
720  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &DevFuncs,
721  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<const FunctionDecl *> &Recursive) {
722  DeviceFunctions.insert(DevFuncs.begin(), DevFuncs.end());
723  RecursiveFunctions.insert(Recursive.begin(), Recursive.end());
724  }
725 
726 public:
727  DeviceFunctionTracker(SemaSYCL &S) : SemaSYCLRef(S) {
728  CG.setSkipConstantExpressions(S.getASTContext());
729  CG.addToCallGraph(S.getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl());
730  CollectSyclExternalFuncs();
731  }
732 
733  ~DeviceFunctionTracker() {
734  DiagDeviceFunction Diagnoser{SemaSYCLRef, RecursiveFunctions};
735  for (const FunctionDecl *FD : DeviceFunctions)
736  if (const FunctionDecl *Def = FD->getDefinition())
737  Diagnoser.CheckBody(Def->getBody());
738  }
739 };
740 
741 /// This function checks whether given DeclContext contains a topmost
742 /// namespace with name "sycl".
743 static bool isDeclaredInSYCLNamespace(const Decl *D) {
744  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext()->getEnclosingNamespaceContext();
745  const auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC);
746  // If this is not a namespace, then we are done.
747  if (!ND)
748  return false;
749 
750  // While it is a namespace, find its parent scope.
751  while (const DeclContext *Parent = ND->getParent()) {
752  if (!isa<NamespaceDecl>(Parent))
753  break;
754  ND = cast<NamespaceDecl>(Parent);
755  }
756 
757  return ND && ND->getName() == "sycl";
758 }
759 
760 // This type does the heavy lifting for the management of device functions,
761 // recursive function detection, and attribute collection for a single
762 // kernel/external function. It walks the callgraph to find all functions that
763 // are called, marks the recursive-functions, and figures out the list of
764 // attributes that apply to this kernel.
765 //
766 // Upon destruction, this type updates the DeviceFunctionTracker.
767 class SingleDeviceFunctionTracker {
768  DeviceFunctionTracker &Parent;
769  FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel = nullptr;
770  FunctionDecl *KernelBody = nullptr;
771  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> DeviceFunctions;
772  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const FunctionDecl *, 16> RecursiveFunctions;
773  llvm::SmallVector<Attr *> CollectedAttributes;
774 
775  FunctionDecl *GetFDFromNode(CallGraphNode *Node) {
776  FunctionDecl *FD = Node->getDecl()->getAsFunction();
777  if (!FD)
778  return nullptr;
779 
780  return FD->getMostRecentDecl();
781  }
782 
783  void VisitCallNode(CallGraphNode *Node, FunctionDecl *CurrentDecl,
784  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<FunctionDecl *> &CallStack) {
785  // If this isn't a function, I don't think there is anything we can do here.
786  if (!CurrentDecl)
787  return;
788 
789  // Determine if this is a recursive function. If so, we're done.
790  if (llvm::is_contained(CallStack, CurrentDecl)) {
791  RecursiveFunctions.insert(CurrentDecl->getCanonicalDecl());
792  return;
793  }
794 
795  // If this is a routine that is not defined and it does not have either
796  // a SYCLKernel or SYCLDevice attribute on it, add it to the set of
797  // routines potentially reachable on device. This is to diagnose such
798  // cases later in finalizeSYCLDelayedAnalysis().
799  if (!CurrentDecl->isDefined() && !CurrentDecl->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>() &&
800  !CurrentDecl->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>())
801  Parent.SemaSYCLRef.addFDToReachableFromSyclDevice(CurrentDecl,
802  CallStack.back());
803 
804  // If this is a parallel_for_work_item that is declared in the
805  // sycl namespace, mark it with the WorkItem scope attribute.
806  // Note: Here, we assume that this is called from within a
807  // parallel_for_work_group; it is undefined to call it otherwise.
808  // We deliberately do not diagnose a violation.
809  if (CurrentDecl->getIdentifier() &&
810  CurrentDecl->getIdentifier()->getName() == "parallel_for_work_item" &&
811  isDeclaredInSYCLNamespace(CurrentDecl) &&
812  !CurrentDecl->hasAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>()) {
813  CurrentDecl->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(
814  Parent.SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkItem));
815  }
816 
817  // We previously thought we could skip this function if we'd seen it before,
818  // but if we haven't seen it before in this call graph, we can end up
819  // missing a recursive call. SO, we have to revisit call-graphs we've
820  // already seen, just in case it ALSO has recursion. For example:
821  // void recurse1();
822  // void recurse2() { recurse1(); }
823  // void recurse1() { recurse2(); }
824  // void CallerInKernel() { recurse1(); recurse2(); }
825  // When checking 'recurse1', we'd have ended up 'visiting' recurse2 without
826  // realizing it was recursive, since we never went into the
827  // child-of-its-child, since THAT was recursive and exited early out of
828  // necessity.
829  // Then when we go to visit the kernel's call to recurse2, we would
830  // immediately escape not noticing it was recursive. SO, we have to do a
831  // little extra work in this case, and make sure we visit the entire call
832  // graph.
833  DeviceFunctions.insert(CurrentDecl);
834 
835  // Collect attributes for functions that aren't the root kernel.
836  if (!CallStack.empty()) {
837  bool DirectlyCalled = CallStack.size() == 1;
838  collectSYCLAttributes(Parent.SemaSYCLRef, CurrentDecl,
839  CollectedAttributes, DirectlyCalled);
840  }
841 
842  // Calculate the kernel body. Note the 'isSYCLKernelBodyFunction' only
843  // tests that it is operator(), so hopefully this doesn't get us too many
844  // false-positives.
845  if (isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(CurrentDecl)) {
846  // This is a direct callee of the kernel.
847  if (CallStack.size() == 1 &&
848  CallStack.back()->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>()) {
849  assert(!KernelBody && "inconsistent call graph - only one kernel body "
850  "function can be called");
851  KernelBody = CurrentDecl;
852  } else if (CallStack.size() == 2 && KernelBody == CallStack.back()) {
853  // To implement rounding-up of a parallel-for range the
854  // SYCL header implementation modifies the kernel call like this:
855  // auto Wrapper = [=](TransformedArgType Arg) {
856  // if (Arg[0] >= NumWorkItems[0])
857  // return;
858  // Arg.set_allowed_range(NumWorkItems);
859  // KernelFunc(Arg);
860  // };
861  //
862  // This transformation leads to a condition where a kernel body
863  // function becomes callable from a new kernel body function.
864  // Hence this test.
865  // FIXME: We need to be more selective here, this can be hit by simply
866  // having a kernel lambda with a lambda call inside of it.
867  KernelBody = CurrentDecl;
868  }
869  }
870 
871  // Recurse.
872  CallStack.push_back(CurrentDecl);
873  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> SeenCallees;
874  for (CallGraphNode *CI : Node->callees()) {
875  FunctionDecl *CurFD = GetFDFromNode(CI);
876 
877  // Make sure we only visit each callee 1x from this function to avoid very
878  // time consuming template recursion cases.
879  if (!llvm::is_contained(SeenCallees, CurFD)) {
880  VisitCallNode(CI, CurFD, CallStack);
881  SeenCallees.insert(CurFD);
882  }
883  }
884  CallStack.pop_back();
885  }
886 
887  // Function to walk the call graph and identify the important information.
888  void Init() {
889  CallGraphNode *KernelNode = Parent.getNodeForKernel(SYCLKernel);
890  llvm::SmallVector<FunctionDecl *> CallStack;
891  VisitCallNode(KernelNode, GetFDFromNode(KernelNode), CallStack);
892 
893  // Always inline the KernelBody in the kernel entry point. For ESIMD
894  // inlining is handled later down the pipeline.
895  if (KernelBody &&
896  Parent.SemaSYCLRef.getLangOpts().SYCLForceInlineKernelLambda &&
897  !KernelBody->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>() &&
898  !KernelBody->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
899  !KernelBody->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>()) {
900  KernelBody->addAttr(AlwaysInlineAttr::CreateImplicit(
901  KernelBody->getASTContext(), {}, AlwaysInlineAttr::Keyword_forceinline));
902  }
903  }
904 
905 public:
906  SingleDeviceFunctionTracker(DeviceFunctionTracker &P, Decl *Kernel)
907  : Parent(P), SYCLKernel(Kernel->getAsFunction()) {
908  Init();
909  }
910 
911  FunctionDecl *GetSYCLKernel() { return SYCLKernel; }
912 
913  FunctionDecl *GetKernelBody() { return KernelBody; }
914 
915  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Attr *> &GetCollectedAttributes() {
916  return CollectedAttributes;
917  }
918 
919  llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &GetDeviceFunctions() {
920  return DeviceFunctions;
921  }
922 
923  ~SingleDeviceFunctionTracker() {
924  Parent.AddSingleFunction(DeviceFunctions, RecursiveFunctions);
925  }
926 };
927 
928 class KernelBodyTransform : public TreeTransform<KernelBodyTransform> {
929 public:
930  KernelBodyTransform(std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> &MPair,
931  Sema &S)
932  : TreeTransform<KernelBodyTransform>(S), MappingPair(MPair), SemaRef(S) {}
933  bool AlwaysRebuild() { return true; }
934 
935  ExprResult TransformDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *DRE) {
936  auto Ref = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
937  if (Ref && Ref == MappingPair.first) {
938  auto NewDecl = MappingPair.second;
939  return DeclRefExpr::Create(
940  SemaRef.getASTContext(), DRE->getQualifierLoc(),
941  DRE->getTemplateKeywordLoc(), NewDecl, false, DRE->getNameInfo(),
942  NewDecl->getType(), DRE->getValueKind());
943  }
944  return DRE;
945  }
946 
947 private:
948  std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> MappingPair;
949  Sema &SemaRef;
950 };
951 
952 class MarkWIScopeFnVisitor : public RecursiveASTVisitor<MarkWIScopeFnVisitor> {
953 public:
954  MarkWIScopeFnVisitor(ASTContext &Ctx) : Ctx(Ctx) {}
955 
956  bool VisitCXXMemberCallExpr(CXXMemberCallExpr *Call) {
957  FunctionDecl *Callee = Call->getDirectCallee();
958  if (!Callee)
959  // not a direct call - continue search
960  return true;
961  QualType Ty = Ctx.getRecordType(Call->getRecordDecl());
962  if (!SemaSYCL::isSyclType(Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::group))
963  // not a member of sycl::group - continue search
964  return true;
965  auto Name = Callee->getName();
966  if (Name != "wait_for" ||
967  Callee->hasAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>())
968  return true;
969  // it is a call to sycl::group::wait_for - mark the callee
970  Callee->addAttr(
971  SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkItem));
972  // continue search as there can be other wait_for calls
973  return true;
974  }
975 
976 private:
977  ASTContext &Ctx;
978 };

980 static bool isSYCLPrivateMemoryVar(VarDecl *VD) {
981  return SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::private_memory);
982 }
983 
984 static void addScopeAttrToLocalVars(CXXMethodDecl &F) {
985  for (Decl *D : F.decls()) {
986  VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
987 
988  if (!VD || isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD) ||
989  VD->getStorageDuration() != StorageDuration::SD_Automatic)
990  continue;
991  // Local variables of private_memory type in the WG scope still have WI
992  // scope, all the rest - WG scope. Simple logic
993  // "if no scope than it is WG scope" won't work, because compiler may add
994  // locals not declared in user code (lambda object parameter, byval
995  // arguments) which will result in alloca w/o any attribute, so need WI
996  // scope too.
997  SYCLScopeAttr::Level L = isSYCLPrivateMemoryVar(VD)
998  ? SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkItem
999  : SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkGroup;
1000  VD->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(F.getASTContext(), L));
1001  }
1002 }
1003 
1004 /// Return method by name
1005 static CXXMethodDecl *getMethodByName(const CXXRecordDecl *CRD,
1006  StringRef MethodName) {
1007  CXXMethodDecl *Method;
1008  auto It = std::find_if(CRD->methods().begin(), CRD->methods().end(),
1009  [MethodName](const CXXMethodDecl *Method) {
1010  return Method->getNameAsString() == MethodName;
1011  });
1012  Method = (It != CRD->methods().end()) ? *It : nullptr;
1013  return Method;
1014 }

1016 static KernelInvocationKind
1017 getKernelInvocationKind(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1018  return llvm::StringSwitch<KernelInvocationKind>(KernelCallerFunc->getName())
1019  .Case("kernel_single_task", InvokeSingleTask)
1020  .Case("kernel_parallel_for", InvokeParallelFor)
1021  .Case("kernel_parallel_for_work_group", InvokeParallelForWorkGroup)
1022  .Default(InvokeUnknown);
1023 }

1025 // The SYCL kernel's 'object type' used for diagnostics and naming/mangling is
1026 // the first parameter to a function template using the sycl_kernel
1027 // attribute. In SYCL 1.2.1, this was passed by value,
1028 // and in SYCL 2020, it is passed by reference.
1029 static QualType GetSYCLKernelObjectType(const FunctionDecl *KernelCaller) {
1030  assert(KernelCaller->getNumParams() > 0 && "Insufficient kernel parameters");
1031  QualType KernelParamTy = KernelCaller->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
1032 
1033  // SYCL 2020 kernels are passed by reference.
1034  if (KernelParamTy->isReferenceType())
1035  KernelParamTy = KernelParamTy->getPointeeType();
1036 
1037  // SYCL 1.2.1
1038  return KernelParamTy.getUnqualifiedType();
1039 }

1041 /// Creates a kernel parameter descriptor
1042 /// \param Src field declaration to construct name from
1043 /// \param Ty the desired parameter type
1044 /// \return the constructed descriptor
1045 static ParamDesc makeParamDesc(const FieldDecl *Src, QualType Ty) {
1046  ASTContext &Ctx = Src->getASTContext();
1047  std::string Name = (Twine("_arg_") + Src->getName()).str();
1048  return std::make_tuple(Ty, &Ctx.Idents.get(Name),
1049  Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty));
1050 }
1051 
1052 static ParamDesc makeParamDesc(ASTContext &Ctx, StringRef Name, QualType Ty) {
1053  return std::make_tuple(Ty, &Ctx.Idents.get(Name),
1054  Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty));
1055 }

1057 /// \return the target of given SYCL accessor type
1058 static target getAccessTarget(QualType FieldTy,
1059  const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *AccTy) {
1060  if (SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::local_accessor))
1061  return local;
1062 
1063  return static_cast<target>(
1064  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[3].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
1065 }

1067 // The first template argument to the kernel caller function is used to identify
1068 // the kernel itself.
1069 static QualType calculateKernelNameType(ASTContext &Ctx,
1070  const FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1071  const TemplateArgumentList *TAL =
1072  KernelCallerFunc->getTemplateSpecializationArgs();
1073  assert(TAL && "No template argument info");
1074  return TAL->get(0).getAsType().getCanonicalType();
1075 }
1076 
1077 // Gets a name for the OpenCL kernel function, calculated from the first
1078 // template argument of the kernel caller function.
1079 static std::pair<std::string, std::string>
1080 constructKernelName(SemaSYCL &S, const FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc,
1081  MangleContext &MC) {
1082  QualType KernelNameType =
1083  calculateKernelNameType(S.getASTContext(), KernelCallerFunc);
1084 
1085  SmallString<256> Result;
1086  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Result);
1087 
1088  MC.mangleCanonicalTypeName(KernelNameType, Out);
1089  std::string MangledName(Out.str());
1090 
1091  std::string StableName =
1092  SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(), KernelNameType);
1093 
1094  // For NativeCPU the kernel name is set to the stable GNU-mangled name
1095  // because the default mangling may be different, for example on Windows.
1096  // This is needed for compiling kernels for multiple SYCL targets to ensure
1097  // the same kernel name can be used for kernel lookup in different target
1098  // binaries. This assumes that all SYCL targets use the same mangling
1099  // produced for the stable name.
1100  // Todo: Check if this assumption is valid, and if it would be better
1101  // instead to always compile the NativeCPU device code in GNU mode which
1102  // may cause issues when compiling headers with non-standard extensions
1103  // written for compilers with different C++ ABIs (like MS VS).
1104  if (S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsNativeCPU) {
1105  MangledName = StableName;
1106  }
1107 
1108  return {MangledName, StableName};
1109 }

1111 static bool isDefaultSPIRArch(ASTContext &Context) {
1112  llvm::Triple T = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
1113  if (T.isSPIR() && T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch)
1114  return true;
1115  return false;
1116 }

1118 static ParmVarDecl *getSyclKernelHandlerArg(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc) {
1119  // Specialization constants in SYCL 2020 are not captured by lambda and
1120  // accessed through new optional lambda argument kernel_handler
1121  auto IsHandlerLambda = [](ParmVarDecl *PVD) {
1122  return SemaSYCL::isSyclType(PVD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::kernel_handler);
1123  };
1124 
1125  assert(llvm::count_if(KernelCallerFunc->parameters(), IsHandlerLambda) <= 1 &&
1126  "Multiple kernel_handler parameters");
1127 
1128  auto KHArg = llvm::find_if(KernelCallerFunc->parameters(), IsHandlerLambda);
1129 
1130  return (KHArg != KernelCallerFunc->param_end()) ? *KHArg : nullptr;
1131 }

1133 static bool isReadOnlyAccessor(const TemplateArgument &AccessModeArg) {
1134  const auto *AccessModeArgEnumType =
1135  AccessModeArg.getIntegralType()->castAs<EnumType>();
1136  const EnumDecl *ED = AccessModeArgEnumType->getDecl();
1137 
1138  auto ReadOnly =
1139  llvm::find_if(ED->enumerators(), [&](const EnumConstantDecl *E) {
1140  return E->getName() == "read";
1141  });
1142 
1143  return ReadOnly != ED->enumerator_end() &&
1144  (*ReadOnly)->getInitVal() == AccessModeArg.getAsIntegral();
1145 }

1158 template <> struct bind_param<FieldDecl *const &> { using type = FieldDecl *; };
1159 
1160 template <typename T> using bind_param_t = typename bind_param<T>::type;
1161 
1162 class KernelObjVisitor {
1163  SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef;
1164 
1165  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1166  void VisitUnionImpl(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1167  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1168  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1169  (Handlers.enterUnion(Owner, Parent), 0)...};
1170  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->fields(), Handlers...);
1171  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1172  (Handlers.leaveUnion(Owner, Parent), 0)...};
1173  }
1174 
1175  // These enable handler execution only when previous Handlers succeed.
1176  template <typename... Tn>
1177  bool handleField(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FDTy, Tn &&... tn) {
1178  bool result = true;
1179  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{(result = result && tn(FD, FDTy), 0)...};
1180  return result;
1181  }
1182  template <typename... Tn>
1183  bool handleField(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BD, QualType BDTy, Tn &&... tn) {
1184  bool result = true;
1185  std::initializer_list<int>{(result = result && tn(BD, BDTy), 0)...};
1186  return result;
1187  }
1188 
1189 // This definition using std::bind is necessary because of a gcc 7.x bug.
1190 #define KF_FOR_EACH(FUNC, Item, Qt) \
1191  handleField( \
1192  Item, Qt, \
1193  std::bind(static_cast<bool (std::decay_t<decltype(Handlers)>::*)( \
1194  bind_param_t<decltype(Item)>, QualType)>( \
1195  &std::decay_t<decltype(Handlers)>::FUNC), \
1196  std::ref(Handlers), _1, _2)...)
1197 
1198  // The following simpler definition works with gcc 8.x and later.
1199  //#define KF_FOR_EACH(FUNC) \
1200 // handleField(Field, FieldTy, ([&](FieldDecl *FD, QualType FDTy) { \
1201 // return Handlers.f(FD, FDTy); \
1202 // })...)
1203 
1204  // Parent contains the FieldDecl or CXXBaseSpecifier that was used to enter
1205  // the Wrapper structure that we're currently visiting. Owner is the parent
1206  // type (which doesn't exist in cases where it is a FieldDecl in the
1207  // 'root'), and Wrapper is the current struct being unwrapped.
1208  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1209  void visitComplexRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1210  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1211  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1212  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1213  (Handlers.enterStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1214  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->bases(), Handlers...);
1215  VisitRecordHelper(Wrapper, Wrapper->fields(), Handlers...);
1216  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1217  (Handlers.leaveStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1218  }
1219 
1220  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1221  void visitSimpleRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1222  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1223  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1224  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1225  (Handlers.handleNonDecompStruct(Owner, Parent, RecordTy), 0)...};
1226  }
1227 
1228  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1229  void visitRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1230  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, QualType RecordTy,
1231  HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1232 
1233  template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1234  void VisitUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1235  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper, HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1236 
1237  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1238  void VisitRecordHelper(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1239  clang::CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_range Range,
1240  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1241  for (const auto &Base : Range) {
1242  QualType BaseTy = Base.getType();
1243  // Handle accessor class as base
1244  if (isSyclSpecialType(BaseTy, SemaSYCLRef))
1245  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1246  (Handlers.handleSyclSpecialType(Owner, Base, BaseTy), 0)...};
1247  else
1248  // For all other bases, visit the record
1249  visitRecord(Owner, Base, BaseTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), BaseTy,
1250  Handlers...);
1251  }
1252  }
1253 
1254  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1255  void VisitRecordHelper(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1256  RecordDecl::field_range Range,
1257  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1258  VisitRecordFields(Owner, Handlers...);
1259  }
1260 
1261  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1262  void visitArrayElementImpl(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1263  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1264  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1265  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1266  (Handlers.nextElement(ElementTy, Index), 0)...};
1267  visitField(Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, Handlers...);
1268  }
1269 
1270  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1271  void visitFirstArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1272  QualType ElementTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1273  visitArrayElementImpl(Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, 0, Handlers...);
1274  }
1275  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1276  void visitNthArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1277  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1278  HandlerTys &... Handlers);
1279 
1280  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1281  void visitSimpleArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1282  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1283  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1284  (Handlers.handleSimpleArrayType(Field, ArrayTy), 0)...};
1285  }
1286 
1287  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1288  void visitComplexArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1289  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1290  // Array workflow is:
1291  // handleArrayType
1292  // enterArray
1293  // nextElement
1294  // VisitField (same as before, note that The FieldDecl is the of array
1295  // itself, not the element)
1296  // ... repeat per element, opt-out for duplicates.
1297  // leaveArray
1298 
1299  if (!KF_FOR_EACH(handleArrayType, Field, ArrayTy))
1300  return;
1301 
1302  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
1303  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
1304  assert(CAT && "Should only be called on constant-size array.");
1305  QualType ET = CAT->getElementType();
1306  uint64_t ElemCount = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1307 
1308  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1309  (Handlers.enterArray(Field, ArrayTy, ET), 0)...};
1310 
1311  visitFirstArrayElement(Owner, Field, ET, Handlers...);
1312  for (uint64_t Index = 1; Index < ElemCount; ++Index)
1313  visitNthArrayElement(Owner, Field, ET, Index, Handlers...);
1314 
1315  (void)std::initializer_list<int>{
1316  (Handlers.leaveArray(Field, ArrayTy, ET), 0)...};
1317  }
1318 
1319  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1320  void visitField(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1321  QualType FieldTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1322  if (isSyclSpecialType(FieldTy, SemaSYCLRef))
1323  KF_FOR_EACH(handleSyclSpecialType, Field, FieldTy);
1324  else if (FieldTy->isStructureOrClassType()) {
1325  if (KF_FOR_EACH(handleStructType, Field, FieldTy)) {
1326  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1327  visitRecord(Owner, Field, RD, FieldTy, Handlers...);
1328  }
1329  } else if (FieldTy->isUnionType()) {
1330  if (KF_FOR_EACH(handleUnionType, Field, FieldTy)) {
1331  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1332  VisitUnion(Owner, Field, RD, Handlers...);
1333  }
1334  } else if (FieldTy->isReferenceType())
1335  KF_FOR_EACH(handleReferenceType, Field, FieldTy);
1336  else if (FieldTy->isPointerType())
1337  KF_FOR_EACH(handlePointerType, Field, FieldTy);
1338  else if (FieldTy->isArrayType())
1339  visitArray(Owner, Field, FieldTy, Handlers...);
1340  else if (FieldTy->isScalarType() || FieldTy->isVectorType())
1341  KF_FOR_EACH(handleScalarType, Field, FieldTy);
1342  else
1343  KF_FOR_EACH(handleOtherType, Field, FieldTy);
1344  }
1345 
1346 public:
1347  KernelObjVisitor(SemaSYCL &S) : SemaSYCLRef(S) {}
1348 
1349  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1350  void VisitRecordBases(const CXXRecordDecl *KernelFunctor,
1351  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1352  VisitRecordHelper(KernelFunctor, KernelFunctor->bases(), Handlers...);
1353  }
1354 
1355  // A visitor function that dispatches to functions as defined in
1356  // SyclKernelFieldHandler for the purposes of kernel generation.
1357  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1358  void VisitRecordFields(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1359  for (const auto Field : Owner->fields())
1360  visitField(Owner, Field, Field->getType(), Handlers...);
1361  }
1362 
1363  template <typename... HandlerTys>
1364  void visitArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1365  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &...Handlers);
1366 
1367 #undef KF_FOR_EACH
1368 };
1369 
1370 // A base type that the SYCL OpenCL Kernel construction task uses to implement
1371 // individual tasks.
1372 class SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {
1373 public:
1374  static constexpr const bool VisitUnionBody = false;
1375  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = true;
1376  // Opt-in based on whether we should visit inside simple containers (structs,
1377  // arrays). All of the 'check' types should likely be true, the int-header,
1378  // and kernel decl creation types should not.
1379  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = true;
1380  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainersWithPointer = false;
1381  // Mark these virtual so that we can use override in the implementer classes,
1382  // despite virtual dispatch never being used.
1383 
1384  // SYCL special class can be a base class or a field decl, so both must be
1385  // handled.
1386  virtual bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *,
1387  const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType) {
1388  return true;
1389  }
1390  virtual bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1391 
1392  virtual bool handleStructType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1393  virtual bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1394  virtual bool handleReferenceType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1395  virtual bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1396  virtual bool handleArrayType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1397  virtual bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1398  // Most handlers shouldn't be handling this, just the field checker.
1399  virtual bool handleOtherType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1400 
1401  // Handle a simple struct that doesn't need to be decomposed, only called on
1402  // handlers with VisitInsideSimpleContainers as false. Replaces
1403  // handleStructType, enterStruct, leaveStruct, and visiting of sub-elements.
1404  virtual bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *,
1405  QualType) {
1406  return true;
1407  }
1408  virtual bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *,
1409  const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType) {
1410  return true;
1411  }
1412 
1413  // Instead of handleArrayType, enterArray, leaveArray, and nextElement (plus
1414  // descending down the elements), this function gets called in the event of an
1415  // array containing simple elements (even in the case of an MD array).
1416  virtual bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *, QualType) { return true; }
1417 
1418  // The following are only used for keeping track of where we are in the base
1419  // class/field graph. Int Headers use this to calculate offset, most others
1420  // don't have a need for these.
1421 
1422  virtual bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) {
1423  return true;
1424  }
1425  virtual bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) {
1426  return true;
1427  }
1428  virtual bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1429  QualType) {
1430  return true;
1431  }
1432  virtual bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1433  QualType) {
1434  return true;
1435  }
1436  virtual bool enterUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *) { return true; }
1437  virtual bool leaveUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *) { return true; }
1438 
1439  // The following are used for stepping through array elements.
1440  virtual bool enterArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) {
1441  return true;
1442  }
1443  virtual bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) {
1444  return true;
1445  }
1446 
1447  virtual bool nextElement(QualType, uint64_t) { return true; }
1448 
1449  virtual ~SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase() = default;
1450 };
1451 
1452 // A class to act as the direct base for all the SYCL OpenCL Kernel construction
1453 // tasks that contains a reference to Sema (and potentially any other
1454 // universally required data).
1455 class SyclKernelFieldHandler : public SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {
1456 protected:
1457  SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef;
1458  SyclKernelFieldHandler(SemaSYCL &S) : SemaSYCLRef(S) {}
1459 
1460  // Returns 'true' if the thing we're visiting (Based on the FD/QualType pair)
1461  // is an element of an array. FD will always be the array field. When
1462  // traversing the array field, Ty will be the type of the array field or the
1463  // type of array element (or some decomposed type from array).
1464  bool isArrayElement(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) const {
1465  return !SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().hasSameType(FD->getType(), Ty);
1466  }
1467 };
1468 
1469 // A class to represent the 'do nothing' case for filtering purposes.
1470 class SyclEmptyHandler final : public SyclKernelFieldHandlerBase {};
1471 SyclEmptyHandler GlobalEmptyHandler;
1472 
1473 template <bool Keep, typename H> struct HandlerFilter;
1474 template <typename H> struct HandlerFilter<true, H> {
1475  H &Handler;
1476  HandlerFilter(H &Handler) : Handler(Handler) {}
1477 };
1478 template <typename H> struct HandlerFilter<false, H> {
1479  SyclEmptyHandler &Handler = GlobalEmptyHandler;
1480  HandlerFilter(H &Handler) {}
1481 };
1482 
1483 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AnyTrue;
1484 
1485 template <bool B> struct AnyTrue<B> { static constexpr bool Value = B; };
1486 
1487 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AnyTrue {
1488  static constexpr bool Value = B || AnyTrue<Rest...>::Value;
1489 };
1490 
1491 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AllTrue;
1492 
1493 template <bool B> struct AllTrue<B> { static constexpr bool Value = B; };
1494 
1495 template <bool B, bool... Rest> struct AllTrue {
1496  static constexpr bool Value = B && AllTrue<Rest...>::Value;
1497 };
1498 
1499 template <typename ParentTy, typename... Handlers>
1500 void KernelObjVisitor::VisitUnion(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1501  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper,
1502  Handlers &... handlers) {
1503  // Don't continue descending if none of the handlers 'care'. This could be 'if
1504  // constexpr' starting in C++17. Until then, we have to count on the
1505  // optimizer to realize "if (false)" is a dead branch.
1506  if (AnyTrue<Handlers::VisitUnionBody...>::Value)
1507  VisitUnionImpl(
1508  Owner, Parent, Wrapper,
1509  HandlerFilter<Handlers::VisitUnionBody, Handlers>(handlers).Handler...);
1510 }
1511 
1512 template <typename... Handlers>
1513 void KernelObjVisitor::visitNthArrayElement(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner,
1514  FieldDecl *ArrayField,
1515  QualType ElementTy, uint64_t Index,
1516  Handlers &... handlers) {
1517  // Don't continue descending if none of the handlers 'care'. This could be 'if
1518  // constexpr' starting in C++17. Until then, we have to count on the
1519  // optimizer to realize "if (false)" is a dead branch.
1520  if (AnyTrue<Handlers::VisitNthArrayElement...>::Value)
1521  visitArrayElementImpl(
1522  Owner, ArrayField, ElementTy, Index,
1523  HandlerFilter<Handlers::VisitNthArrayElement, Handlers>(handlers)
1524  .Handler...);
1525 }
1526 
1527 template <typename ParentTy, typename... HandlerTys>
1528 void KernelObjVisitor::visitRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, ParentTy &Parent,
1529  const CXXRecordDecl *Wrapper,
1530  QualType RecordTy,
1531  HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1532  RecordDecl *RD = RecordTy->getAsRecordDecl();
1533  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1534  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>()) {
1535  // If this container requires decomposition, we have to visit it as
1536  // 'complex', so all handlers are called in this case with the 'complex'
1537  // case.
1538  visitComplexRecord(Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy, Handlers...);
1539  } else if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainersWithPointer...>::
1540  Value) {
1541  // We are currently in PointerHandler visitor.
1542  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>()) {
1543  // This is a record containing pointers.
1544  visitComplexRecord(Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy, Handlers...);
1545  } else {
1546  // This is a record without pointers.
1547  visitSimpleRecord(Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy, Handlers...);
1548  }
1549  } else {
1550  // "Simple" Containers are those that do NOT need to be decomposed,
1551  // "Complex" containers are those that DO. In the case where the container
1552  // does NOT need to be decomposed, we can call VisitSimpleRecord on the
1553  // handlers that have opted-out of VisitInsideSimpleContainers. The 'if'
1554  // makes sure we only do that if at least 1 has opted out.
1555  if (!AllTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1556  visitSimpleRecord(
1557  Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy,
1558  HandlerFilter<!HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1559  Handlers)
1560  .Handler...);
1561 
1562  // Even though this is a 'simple' container, some handlers (via
1563  // VisitInsideSimpleContainers = true) need to treat it as if it needs
1564  // decomposing, so we call VisitComplexRecord iif at least one has.
1565  if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1566  visitComplexRecord(
1567  Owner, Parent, Wrapper, RecordTy,
1568  HandlerFilter<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1569  Handlers)
1570  .Handler...);
1571  }
1572 }
1573 
1574 template <typename... HandlerTys>
1575 void KernelObjVisitor::visitArray(const CXXRecordDecl *Owner, FieldDecl *Field,
1576  QualType ArrayTy, HandlerTys &... Handlers) {
1577 
1578  if (Field->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>()) {
1579  visitComplexArray(Owner, Field, ArrayTy, Handlers...);
1580  } else if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainersWithPointer...>::
1581  Value) {
1582  // We are currently in PointerHandler visitor.
1583  if (Field->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>()) {
1584  // This is an array of pointers, or an array of a type containing
1585  // pointers.
1586  visitComplexArray(Owner, Field, ArrayTy, Handlers...);
1587  } else {
1588  // This is an array which does not contain pointers.
1589  visitSimpleArray(Owner, Field, ArrayTy, Handlers...);
1590  }
1591  } else {
1592  if (!AllTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1593  visitSimpleArray(
1594  Owner, Field, ArrayTy,
1595  HandlerFilter<!HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1596  Handlers)
1597  .Handler...);
1598 
1599  if (AnyTrue<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers...>::Value)
1600  visitComplexArray(
1601  Owner, Field, ArrayTy,
1602  HandlerFilter<HandlerTys::VisitInsideSimpleContainers, HandlerTys>(
1603  Handlers)
1604  .Handler...);
1605  }
1606 }
1607 
1608 // A type to check the validity of all of the argument types.
1609 class SyclKernelFieldChecker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1610  bool IsInvalid = false;
1611  DiagnosticsEngine &Diag;
1612  // Keeps track of whether we are currently handling fields inside a struct.
1613  // Fields of kernel functor or direct kernel captures will have a depth 0.
1614  int StructFieldDepth = 0;
1615  // Initialize with -1 so that fields of a base class of the kernel functor
1616  // has depth 0. Visitor method enterStruct increments this to 0 when the base
1617  // class is entered.
1618  int StructBaseDepth = -1;
1619 
1620  // Check whether the object should be disallowed from being copied to kernel.
1621  // Return true if not copyable, false if copyable.
1622  bool checkNotCopyableToKernel(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
1623  if (FieldTy->isArrayType()) {
1624  if (const auto *CAT =
1625  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(FieldTy)) {
1626  QualType ET = CAT->getElementType();
1627  return checkNotCopyableToKernel(FD, ET);
1628  }
1629  return Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(),
1630  diag::err_sycl_non_constant_array_type)
1631  << FieldTy;
1632  }
1633 
1634  return false;
1635  }
1636 
1637  bool checkPropertyListType(TemplateArgument PropList, SourceLocation Loc) {
1638  if (PropList.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Type)
1639  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1640  Loc, diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_template_param);
1641 
1642  QualType PropListTy = PropList.getAsType();
1643  if (!SemaSYCL::isSyclType(PropListTy, SYCLTypeAttr::accessor_property_list))
1644  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1645  Loc, diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_template_param);
1646 
1647  const auto *AccPropListDecl =
1648  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropListTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1649  if (AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs().size() != 1)
1650  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(Loc,
1651  diag::err_sycl_invalid_property_list_param_number)
1652  << "accessor_property_list";
1653 
1654  const auto TemplArg = AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1655  if (TemplArg.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Pack)
1656  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1657  Loc,
1658  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1659  << /*accessor_property_list*/ 0 << /*parameter pack*/ 0;
1660 
1661  for (TemplateArgument::pack_iterator Prop = TemplArg.pack_begin();
1662  Prop != TemplArg.pack_end(); ++Prop) {
1663  if (Prop->getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Type)
1664  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1665  Loc,
1666  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1667  << /*accessor_property_list pack argument*/ 1 << /*type*/ 1;
1668  QualType PropTy = Prop->getAsType();
1669  if (isAccessorPropertyType(PropTy, SYCLTypeAttr::buffer_location) &&
1670  checkBufferLocationType(PropTy, Loc))
1671  return true;
1672  }
1673  return false;
1674  }
1675 
1676  bool checkBufferLocationType(QualType PropTy, SourceLocation Loc) {
1677  const auto *PropDecl =
1678  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropTy->getAsRecordDecl());
1679  if (PropDecl->getTemplateArgs().size() != 1)
1680  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(Loc,
1681  diag::err_sycl_invalid_property_list_param_number)
1682  << "buffer_location";
1683 
1684  const auto BufferLoc = PropDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
1685  if (BufferLoc.getKind() != TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Integral)
1686  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1687  Loc,
1688  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1689  << /*buffer_location*/ 2 << /*non-negative integer*/ 2;
1690 
1691  int LocationID = static_cast<int>(BufferLoc.getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
1692  if (LocationID < 0)
1693  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(
1694  Loc,
1695  diag::err_sycl_invalid_accessor_property_list_template_param)
1696  << /*buffer_location*/ 2 << /*non-negative integer*/ 2;
1697 
1698  return false;
1699  }
1700 
1701  bool checkSyclSpecialType(QualType Ty, SourceRange Loc) {
1702  assert(isSyclSpecialType(Ty, SemaSYCLRef) &&
1703  "Should only be called on sycl special class types.");
1704 
1705  // Annotated pointers and annotated arguments must be captured
1706  // directly by the SYCL kernel.
1707  if ((SemaSYCL::isSyclType(Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::annotated_ptr) ||
1708  SemaSYCL::isSyclType(Ty, SYCLTypeAttr::annotated_arg)) &&
1709  (StructFieldDepth > 0 || StructBaseDepth > 0))
1710  return SemaSYCLRef.Diag(Loc.getBegin(),
1711  diag::err_bad_kernel_param_data_members)
1712  << Ty << /*Struct*/ 1;
1713 
1714  const RecordDecl *RecD = Ty->getAsRecordDecl();
1715  if (const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *CTSD =
1716  dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecD)) {
1717  const TemplateArgumentList &TAL = CTSD->getTemplateArgs();
1718  TemplateArgument TA = TAL.get(0);
1719 
1720  // Parameter packs are used by properties so they are always valid.
1721  if (TA.getKind() != TemplateArgument::Pack) {
1722  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited;
1723  checkSYCLType(SemaSYCLRef, TA.getAsType(), Loc, Visited);
1724  }
1725 
1726  if (TAL.size() > 5)
1727  return checkPropertyListType(TAL.get(5), Loc.getBegin());
1728  }
1729  return false;
1730  }
1731 
1732 public:
1733  SyclKernelFieldChecker(SemaSYCL &S)
1734  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), Diag(S.getASTContext().getDiagnostics()) {}
1735  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1736  bool isValid() { return !IsInvalid; }
1737 
1738  bool handleReferenceType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1739  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_bad_kernel_param_type) << FieldTy;
1740  IsInvalid = true;
1741  return isValid();
1742  }
1743 
1744  bool handleStructType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1745  CXXRecordDecl *RD = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1746  assert(RD && "Not a RecordDecl inside the handler for struct type");
1747  if (RD->isLambda()) {
1748  for (const LambdaCapture &LC : RD->captures())
1749  if (LC.capturesThis() && LC.isImplicit()) {
1750  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(LC.getLocation(), diag::err_implicit_this_capture);
1751  IsInvalid = true;
1752  }
1753  }
1754  return isValid();
1755  }
1756 
1757  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
1758  QualType FieldTy) final {
1759  IsInvalid |= checkSyclSpecialType(FieldTy, BS.getBeginLoc());
1760  return isValid();
1761  }
1762 
1763  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1764  IsInvalid |= checkSyclSpecialType(FieldTy, FD->getLocation());
1765  return isValid();
1766  }
1767 
1768  bool handleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1769  IsInvalid |= checkNotCopyableToKernel(FD, FieldTy);
1770  return isValid();
1771  }
1772 
1773  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1774  while (FieldTy->isAnyPointerType()) {
1775  FieldTy = QualType{FieldTy->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(), 0};
1776  if (FieldTy->isVariableArrayType()) {
1777  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_vla_unsupported) << 0;
1778  IsInvalid = true;
1779  break;
1780  }
1781  }
1782  return isValid();
1783  }
1784 
1785  bool handleOtherType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
1786  Diag.Report(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_bad_kernel_param_type) << FieldTy;
1787  IsInvalid = true;
1788  return isValid();
1789  }
1790 
1791  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1792  ++StructFieldDepth;
1793  return true;
1794  }
1795 
1796  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1797  --StructFieldDepth;
1798  return true;
1799  }
1800 
1801  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
1802  QualType FieldTy) final {
1803  ++StructBaseDepth;
1804  return true;
1805  }
1806 
1807  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
1808  QualType FieldTy) final {
1809  --StructBaseDepth;
1810  return true;
1811  }
1812 };

1814 // A type to check the validity of accessing accessor/sampler/stream

1820

1826  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1827
