1857 // A type to mark whether a collection requires decomposition
1858 // or needs to be transformed to a new type. If a collection
1859 // contains pointers, and is not decomposed, a new type must
1860 // be generated with all pointers in global address space.
1861 class SyclKernelDecompMarker : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
1862  llvm::SmallVector<bool, 16> CollectionStack;
1863  llvm::SmallVector<bool, 16> PointerStack;
1864 
1865 public:
1866  static constexpr const bool VisitUnionBody = false;
1867  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
1868 
1869  SyclKernelDecompMarker(SemaSYCL &S) : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S) {
1870  // In order to prevent checking this over and over, just add a dummy-base
1871  // entry.
1872  CollectionStack.push_back(true);
1873  PointerStack.push_back(true);
1874  }
1875 
1876  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1877  QualType) final {
1878  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1879  return true;
1880  }
1881  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1882  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1883  return true;
1884  }
1885 
1886  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1887  PointerStack.back() = true;
1888  return true;
1889  }
1890 
1891  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType) final {
1892  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1893  PointerStack.push_back(false);
1894  return true;
1895  }
1896 
1897  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType Ty) final {
1898  // If a record needs to be decomposed, it is marked with
1899  // SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr. Else if a record contains
1900  // a pointer, it is marked with SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr. A record
1901  // will never be marked with both attributes.
1902  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1903  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1904  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1905  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1906  RD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1907  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1908  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1909  PointerStack.pop_back();
1910  } else if (PointerStack.pop_back_val()) {
1911  PointerStack.back() = true;
1912  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
1913  RD->addAttr(SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr::CreateImplicit(
1914  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1915  }
1916  return true;
1917  }
1918 
1919  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1920  QualType) final {
1921  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1922  PointerStack.push_back(false);
1923  return true;
1924  }
1925 
1926  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
1927  QualType Ty) final {
1928  // If a record needs to be decomposed, it is marked with
1929  // SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr. Else if a record contains
1930  // a pointer, it is marked with SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr. A record
1931  // will never be marked with both attributes.
1932  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1933  assert(RD && "should not be null.");
1934  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1935  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1936  RD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1937  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1938  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1939  PointerStack.pop_back();
1940  } else if (PointerStack.pop_back_val()) {
1941  PointerStack.back() = true;
1942  if (!RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
1943  RD->addAttr(SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr::CreateImplicit(
1944  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1945  }
1946  return true;
1947  }
1948 
1949  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) final {
1950  CollectionStack.push_back(false);
1951  PointerStack.push_back(false);
1952  return true;
1953  }
1954 
1955  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ElementTy) final {
1956  // If an array needs to be decomposed, it is marked with
1957  // SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr. Else if the array is an array of pointers
1958  // or an array of structs containing pointers, it is marked with
1959  // SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr. An array will never be marked with both
1960  // attributes.
1961  if (CollectionStack.pop_back_val()) {
1962  // Cannot assert, since in MD arrays we'll end up marking them multiple
1963  // times.
1964  if (!FD->hasAttr<SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr>())
1965  FD->addAttr(SYCLRequiresDecompositionAttr::CreateImplicit(
1966  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1967  CollectionStack.back() = true;
1968  PointerStack.pop_back();
1969  } else if (PointerStack.pop_back_val()) {
1970  if (!FD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
1971  FD->addAttr(SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr::CreateImplicit(
1972  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
1973  PointerStack.back() = true;
1974  }
1975  return true;
1976  }
1977 };
1978 
1979 static QualType ModifyAddressSpace(SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef, QualType Ty) {
1980  // USM allows to use raw pointers instead of buffers/accessors, but these
1981  // pointers point to the specially allocated memory. For pointer fields,
1982  // except for function pointer fields, we add a kernel argument with the
1983  // same type as field but global address space, because OpenCL requires it.
1984  // Function pointers should have program address space. This is set in
1985  // CodeGen.
1986  QualType PointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
1987  Qualifiers Quals = PointeeTy.getQualifiers();
1988  LangAS AS = Quals.getAddressSpace();
1989  // Leave global_device and global_host address spaces as is to help FPGA
1990  // device in memory allocations.
1991  if (!PointeeTy->isFunctionType() && AS != LangAS::sycl_global_device &&
1992  AS != LangAS::sycl_global_host)
1993  Quals.setAddressSpace(LangAS::sycl_global);
1994  PointeeTy = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getQualifiedType(
1995  PointeeTy.getUnqualifiedType(), Quals);
1996  return SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getPointerType(PointeeTy);
1997 }
1998 
1999 // This visitor is used to traverse a non-decomposed record/array to
2000 // generate a new type corresponding to this record/array.
2001 class SyclKernelPointerHandler : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2002  llvm::SmallVector<CXXRecordDecl *, 8> ModifiedRecords;
2003  SmallVector<CXXBaseSpecifier *, 8> ModifiedBases;
2004  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray;
2005 
2006  IdentifierInfo *getModifiedName(IdentifierInfo *Id) {
2007  std::string Name =
2008  Id ? (Twine("__generated_") + Id->getName()).str() : "__generated_";
2009  return &SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().Idents.get(Name);
2010  }
2011 
2012  // Create Decl for the new type we are generating.
2013  // The fields (and base classes) of this record will be generated as
2014  // the visitor traverses kernel object record fields.
2015  void createNewType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2016  auto *ModifiedRD = CXXRecordDecl::Create(
2017  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), RD->getTagKind(),
2018  const_cast<DeclContext *>(RD->getDeclContext()), SourceLocation(),
2019  SourceLocation(), getModifiedName(RD->getIdentifier()));
2020  ModifiedRD->startDefinition();
2021  if (RD->hasAttrs())
2022  ModifiedRD->setAttrs(RD->getAttrs());
2023  ModifiedRecords.push_back(ModifiedRD);
2024  }
2025 
2026  // Create and add FieldDecl for FieldTy to generated record.
2027  void addField(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
2028  assert(!ModifiedRecords.empty() &&
2029  "ModifiedRecords should have at least 1 record");
2030  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2031  auto *Field = FieldDecl::Create(
2032  Ctx, ModifiedRecords.back(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
2033  getModifiedName(FD->getIdentifier()), FieldTy,
2034  Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(FieldTy, SourceLocation()), /*BW=*/nullptr,
2035  /*Mutable=*/false, ICIS_NoInit);
2036  Field->setAccess(FD->getAccess());
2037  if (FD->hasAttrs())
2038  Field->setAttrs(FD->getAttrs());
2039  // Add generated field to generated record.
2040  ModifiedRecords.back()->addDecl(Field);
2041  }
2042 
2043  void createBaseSpecifier(const CXXRecordDecl *Parent, const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2044  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS) {
2045  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo =
2046  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(
2047  QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0), SourceLocation());
2048  CXXBaseSpecifier *ModifiedBase = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.CheckBaseSpecifier(
2049  const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(Parent), SourceRange(), BS.isVirtual(),
2050  BS.getAccessSpecifier(), TInfo, SourceLocation());
2051  ModifiedBases.push_back(ModifiedBase);
2052  }
2053 
2054  CXXRecordDecl *getGeneratedNewRecord(const CXXRecordDecl *OldBaseDecl) {
2055  // At this point we have finished generating fields for the new
2056  // class corresponding to OldBaseDecl. Pop out the generated
2057  // record.
2058  CXXRecordDecl *ModifiedRD = ModifiedRecords.pop_back_val();
2059  ModifiedRD->completeDefinition();
2060  // Check the 'old' class for base classes.
2061  // Set bases classes for newly generated class if it has any.
2062  if (OldBaseDecl->getNumBases() > 0) {
2063  SmallVector<CXXBaseSpecifier *, 8> BasesForGeneratedClass;
2064  for (size_t I = 0; I < OldBaseDecl->getNumBases(); ++I)
2065  BasesForGeneratedClass.insert(BasesForGeneratedClass.begin(),
2066  ModifiedBases.pop_back_val());
2067  ModifiedRD->setBases(BasesForGeneratedClass.data(),
2068  OldBaseDecl->getNumBases());
2069  }
2070  return ModifiedRD;
2071  }
2072 
2073 public:
2074  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainersWithPointer = true;
2075  static constexpr const bool VisitNthArrayElement = false;
2076  SyclKernelPointerHandler(SemaSYCL &S, const CXXRecordDecl *RD)
2077  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S) {
2078  createNewType(RD);
2079  }
2080 
2081  SyclKernelPointerHandler(SemaSYCL &S) : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S) {}
2082 
2083  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *, QualType Ty) final {
2084  createNewType(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2085  return true;
2086  }
2087 
2088  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
2089  CXXRecordDecl *ModifiedRD = getGeneratedNewRecord(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2090 
2091  // Add this record as a field of it's parent record if it is not an
2092  // array element.
2093  if (!isArrayElement(FD, Ty))
2094  addField(FD, QualType(ModifiedRD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
2095  else
2096  ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.push_back(
2097  QualType(ModifiedRD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
2098 
2099  return true;
2100  }
2101 
2102  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &,
2103  QualType Ty) final {
2104  createNewType(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2105  return true;
2106  }
2107 
2108  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *Parent, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2109  QualType Ty) final {
2110  CXXRecordDecl *ModifiedRD = getGeneratedNewRecord(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2111 
2112  // Create CXXBaseSpecifier for this generated class.
2113  createBaseSpecifier(Parent, ModifiedRD, BS);
2114  return true;
2115  }
2116 
2117  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType ET) final {
2118  QualType ModifiedArrayElement = ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.pop_back_val();
2119 
2120  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
2121  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayTy);
2122  assert(CAT && "Should only be called on constant-size array.");
2123  QualType ModifiedArray = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getConstantArrayType(
2124  ModifiedArrayElement, CAT->getSize(),
2125  const_cast<Expr *>(CAT->getSizeExpr()), CAT->getSizeModifier(),
2126  CAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers());
2127 
2128  if (ModifiedRecords.empty()) {
2129  // This is a top-level kernel argument.
2130  ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.push_back(ModifiedArray);
2131  } else if (!isArrayElement(FD, ArrayTy)) {
2132  // Add this array field as a field of it's parent record.
2133  addField(FD, ModifiedArray);
2134  } else {
2135  // Multi-dimensional array element.
2136  ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.push_back(ModifiedArray);
2137  }
2138 
2139  return true;
2140  }
2141 
2142  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2143  QualType ModifiedPointerType = ModifyAddressSpace(SemaSYCLRef, FieldTy);
2144  if (!isArrayElement(FD, FieldTy))
2145  addField(FD, ModifiedPointerType);
2146  else
2147  ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.push_back(ModifiedPointerType);
2148  // We do not need to wrap pointers since this is a pointer inside
2149  // non-decomposed struct.
2150  return true;
2151  }
2152 
2153  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2154  addField(FD, FieldTy);
2155  return true;
2156  }
2157 
2158  bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2159  return handleScalarType(FD, FieldTy);
2160  }
2161 
2162  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD,
2163  QualType Ty) final {
2164  addField(FD, Ty);
2165  return true;
2166  }
2167 
2168  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *Parent,
2169  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) final {
2170  createBaseSpecifier(Parent, Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), BS);
2171  return true;
2172  }
2173 
2174  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
2175  addField(FD, Ty);
2176  return true;
2177  }
2178 
2179 public:
2180  QualType getNewRecordType() {
2181  CXXRecordDecl *ModifiedRD = ModifiedRecords.pop_back_val();
2182  ModifiedRD->completeDefinition();
2183 
2184  if (!ModifiedBases.empty())
2185  ModifiedRD->setBases(ModifiedBases.data(), ModifiedBases.size());
2186 
2187  return QualType(ModifiedRD->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
2188  }
2189  QualType getNewArrayType() {
2190  return ModifiedArrayElementsOrArray.pop_back_val();
2191  }
2192 };
2193 
2194 // A type to Create and own the FunctionDecl for the kernel.
2195 class SyclKernelDeclCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2196  FunctionDecl *KernelDecl;
2197  llvm::SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 8> Params;
2198  Sema::ContextRAII FuncContext;
2199  // Holds the last handled field's first parameter. This doesn't store an
2200  // iterator as push_back invalidates iterators.
2201  size_t LastParamIndex = 0;
2202  // Keeps track of whether we are currently handling fields inside a struct.
2203  int StructDepth = 0;
2204 
2205  void addParam(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
2206  ParamDesc newParamDesc = makeParamDesc(FD, FieldTy);
2207  addParam(newParamDesc, FieldTy);
2208  }
2209 
2210  void addParam(const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType FieldTy) {
2211  // TODO: There is no name for the base available, but duplicate names are
2212  // seemingly already possible, so we'll give them all the same name for now.
2213  // This only happens with the accessor types.
2214  StringRef Name = "_arg__base";
2215  ParamDesc newParamDesc =
2216  makeParamDesc(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), Name, FieldTy);
2217  addParam(newParamDesc, FieldTy);
2218  }
2219  // Add a parameter with specified name and type
2220  void addParam(StringRef Name, QualType ParamTy) {
2221  ParamDesc newParamDesc =
2222  makeParamDesc(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), Name, ParamTy);
2223  addParam(newParamDesc, ParamTy);
2224  }
2225 
2226  void addParam(ParamDesc newParamDesc, QualType FieldTy) {
2227  // Create a new ParmVarDecl based on the new info.
2228  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2229  auto *NewParam = ParmVarDecl::Create(
2230  Ctx, KernelDecl, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
2231  std::get<1>(newParamDesc), std::get<0>(newParamDesc),
2232  std::get<2>(newParamDesc), SC_None, /*DefArg*/ nullptr);
2233  NewParam->setScopeInfo(0, Params.size());
2234  NewParam->setIsUsed();
2235 
2236  LastParamIndex = Params.size();
2237  Params.push_back(NewParam);
2238  }
2239 
2240  // Handle accessor properties. If any properties were found in
2241  // the accessor_property_list - add the appropriate attributes to ParmVarDecl.
2242  void handleAccessorPropertyList(ParmVarDecl *Param,
2243  const CXXRecordDecl *RecordDecl,
2244  SourceLocation Loc) {
2245  const auto *AccTy = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecordDecl);
2246  if (AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() < 6)
2247  return;
2248  const auto PropList = cast<TemplateArgument>(AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[5]);
2249  QualType PropListTy = PropList.getAsType();
2250  const auto *AccPropListDecl =
2251  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropListTy->getAsRecordDecl());
2252  const auto TemplArg = AccPropListDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
2253  // Move through TemplateArgs list of a property list and search for
2254  // properties. If found - apply the appropriate attribute to ParmVarDecl.
2255  for (TemplateArgument::pack_iterator Prop = TemplArg.pack_begin();
2256  Prop != TemplArg.pack_end(); ++Prop) {
2257  QualType PropTy = Prop->getAsType();
2258  if (isAccessorPropertyType(PropTy, SYCLTypeAttr::no_alias))
2259  handleNoAliasProperty(Param, PropTy, Loc);
2260  if (isAccessorPropertyType(PropTy, SYCLTypeAttr::buffer_location))
2261  handleBufferLocationProperty(Param, PropTy, Loc);
2262  }
2263  }
2264 
2265  void handleNoAliasProperty(ParmVarDecl *Param, QualType PropTy,
2266  SourceLocation Loc) {
2267  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2268  Param->addAttr(RestrictAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, Loc));
2269  }
2270 
2271  // Obtain an integer value stored in a template parameter of buffer_location
2272  // property to pass it to buffer_location kernel attribute
2273  void handleBufferLocationProperty(ParmVarDecl *Param, QualType PropTy,
2274  SourceLocation Loc) {
2275  // If we have more than 1 buffer_location properties on a single
2276  // accessor - emit an error
2277  if (Param->hasAttr<SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr>()) {
2278  SemaSYCLRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_compiletime_property_duplication)
2279  << "buffer_location";
2280  return;
2281  }
2282  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2283  const auto *PropDecl =
2284  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(PropTy->getAsRecordDecl());
2285  const auto BufferLoc = PropDecl->getTemplateArgs()[0];
2286  int LocationID = static_cast<int>(BufferLoc.getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
2287  Param->addAttr(
2288  SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr::CreateImplicit(Ctx, LocationID));
2289  }
2290 
2291  // Additional processing is required for accessor type.
2292  void handleAccessorType(QualType FieldTy, const CXXRecordDecl *RecordDecl,
2293  SourceLocation Loc) {
2294  handleAccessorPropertyList(Params.back(), RecordDecl, Loc);
2295 
2296  // If "accessor" type check if read only
2297  if (SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::accessor)) {
2298  // Get access mode of accessor.
2299  const auto *AccessorSpecializationDecl =
2300  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RecordDecl);
2301  const TemplateArgument &AccessModeArg =
2302  AccessorSpecializationDecl->getTemplateArgs().get(2);
2303  if (isReadOnlyAccessor(AccessModeArg))
2304  Params.back()->addAttr(SYCLAccessorReadonlyAttr::CreateImplicit(
2305  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
2306  }
2307 
2308  // Add implicit attribute to parameter decl when it is a read only
2309  // SYCL accessor.
2310  Params.back()->addAttr(
2311  SYCLAccessorPtrAttr::CreateImplicit(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
2312  }
2313 
2314  // All special SYCL objects must have __init method. We extract types for
2315  // kernel parameters from __init method parameters. We will use __init method
2316  // and kernel parameters which we build here to initialize special objects in
2317  // the kernel body.
2318  bool handleSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
2319  const auto *RecordDecl = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2320  assert(RecordDecl && "The type must be a RecordDecl");
2321  llvm::StringLiteral MethodName =
2322  KernelDecl->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() && isSyclAccessorType(FieldTy)
2323  ? InitESIMDMethodName
2324  : InitMethodName;
2325  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(RecordDecl, MethodName);
2326  assert(InitMethod && "The type must have the __init method");
2327 
2328  // Don't do -1 here because we count on this to be the first parameter added
2329  // (if any).
2330  size_t ParamIndex = Params.size();
2331  for (const ParmVarDecl *Param : InitMethod->parameters()) {
2332  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
2333  addParam(FD, ParamTy.getCanonicalType());
2334 
2335  // Propagate add_ir_attributes_kernel_parameter attribute.
2336  if (const auto *AddIRAttr =
2337  Param->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameterAttr>())
2338  Params.back()->addAttr(AddIRAttr->clone(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
2339 
2340  // FIXME: This code is temporary, and will be removed once __init_esimd
2341  // is removed and property list refactored.
2342  // The function handleAccessorType includes a call to
2343  // handleAccessorPropertyList. If new classes with property list are
2344  // added, this code needs to be refactored to call
2345  // handleAccessorPropertyList for each class which requires it.
2346  if (ParamTy.getTypePtr()->isPointerType() && isSyclAccessorType(FieldTy))
2347  handleAccessorType(FieldTy, RecordDecl, FD->getBeginLoc());
2348  }
2349  LastParamIndex = ParamIndex;
2350  return true;
2351  }
2352 
2353  static void setKernelImplicitAttrs(ASTContext &Context, FunctionDecl *FD,
2354  bool IsSIMDKernel) {
2355  // Set implicit attributes.
2356  FD->addAttr(OpenCLKernelAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2357  FD->addAttr(ArtificialAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2358  if (IsSIMDKernel)
2359  FD->addAttr(SYCLSimdAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
2360  }
2361 
2362  static FunctionDecl *createKernelDecl(ASTContext &Ctx, SourceLocation Loc,
2363  bool IsInline, bool IsSIMDKernel) {
2364  // Create this with no prototype, and we can fix this up after we've seen
2365  // all the params.
2366  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo Info(CC_OpenCLKernel);
2367  QualType FuncType = Ctx.getFunctionType(Ctx.VoidTy, {}, Info);
2368 
2369  FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2370  Ctx, Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl(), Loc, Loc, DeclarationName(),
2371  FuncType, Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ctx.VoidTy), SC_None);
2372  FD->setImplicitlyInline(IsInline);
2373  setKernelImplicitAttrs(Ctx, FD, IsSIMDKernel);
2374 
2375  // Add kernel to translation unit to see it in AST-dump.
2376  Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl()->addDecl(FD);
2377  return FD;
2378  }
2379 
2380  // If the record has been marked with SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr,
2381  // it implies that it contains a pointer within. This function
2382  // defines a PointerHandler visitor which visits this record
2383  // recursively and modifies the address spaces of any pointer
2384  // found as required, thereby generating a new record with all
2385  // pointers in 'right' address space. PointerHandler.getNewRecordType()
2386  // returns this generated type.
2387  QualType GenerateNewRecordType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2388  SyclKernelPointerHandler PointerHandler(SemaSYCLRef, RD);
2389  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{SemaSYCLRef};
2390  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(RD, PointerHandler);
2391  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(RD, PointerHandler);
2392  return PointerHandler.getNewRecordType();
2393  }
2394 
2395  // If the array has been marked with SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr,
2396  // it implies that this is an array of pointers, or an array
2397  // of a type which contains pointers. This function generates
2398  // a new array with all pointers in the required address space.
2399  QualType GenerateNewArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
2400  const auto *Owner = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getParent());
2401  SyclKernelPointerHandler PointerHandler(SemaSYCLRef);
2402  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{SemaSYCLRef};
2403  Visitor.visitArray(Owner, FD, FieldTy, PointerHandler);
2404  return PointerHandler.getNewArrayType();
2405  }
2406 
2407 public:
2408  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
2409  SyclKernelDeclCreator(SemaSYCL &S, SourceLocation Loc, bool IsInline,
2410  bool IsSIMDKernel, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel)
2411  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S),
2412  KernelDecl(
2413  createKernelDecl(S.getASTContext(), Loc, IsInline, IsSIMDKernel)),
2414  FuncContext(SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef, KernelDecl) {
2415  S.addSyclOpenCLKernel(SYCLKernel, KernelDecl);
2416 
2417  if (const auto *AddIRAttrFunc =
2418  SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>())
2419  KernelDecl->addAttr(AddIRAttrFunc->clone(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
2420  }
2421 
2422  ~SyclKernelDeclCreator() {
2423  ASTContext &Ctx = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2424  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo Info(CC_OpenCLKernel);
2425 
2426  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ArgTys;
2427  std::transform(std::begin(Params), std::end(Params),
2428  std::back_inserter(ArgTys),
2429  [](const ParmVarDecl *PVD) { return PVD->getType(); });
2430 
2431  QualType FuncType = Ctx.getFunctionType(Ctx.VoidTy, ArgTys, Info);
2432  KernelDecl->setType(FuncType);
2433  KernelDecl->setParams(Params);
2434 
2435  // Make sure that this is marked as a kernel so that the code-gen can make
2436  // decisions based on that. We cannot add this earlier, otherwise the call
2437  // to TransformStmt in replaceWithLocalClone can diagnose something that got
2438  // diagnosed on the actual kernel.
2439  KernelDecl->addAttr(
2440  SYCLKernelAttr::CreateImplicit(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()));
2441 
2442  SemaSYCLRef.addSyclDeviceDecl(KernelDecl);
2443  }

2447  return true;

2451  --StructDepth;

2458  return true;

2462  QualType FieldTy) final {
2463  --StructDepth;
2464  return true;

2467  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2468  QualType FieldTy) final {
2469  const auto *RecordDecl = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2470  assert(RecordDecl && "The type must be a RecordDecl");
2471  llvm::StringLiteral MethodName =
2472  KernelDecl->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() && isSyclAccessorType(FieldTy)
2473  ? InitESIMDMethodName
2474  : InitMethodName;
2475  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(RecordDecl, MethodName);
2476  assert(InitMethod && "The type must have the __init method");
2477 
2478  // Don't do -1 here because we count on this to be the first parameter added
2479  // (if any).
2480  size_t ParamIndex = Params.size();
2481  for (const ParmVarDecl *Param : InitMethod->parameters()) {
2482  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
2483  addParam(BS, ParamTy.getCanonicalType());
2484  // FIXME: This code is temporary, and will be removed once __init_esimd
2485  // is removed and property list refactored.
2486  // The function handleAccessorType includes a call to
2487  // handleAccessorPropertyList. If new classes with property list are
2488  // added, this code needs to be refactored to call
2489  // handleAccessorPropertyList for each class which requires it.
2490  if (ParamTy.getTypePtr()->isPointerType() && isSyclAccessorType(FieldTy))
2491  handleAccessorType(FieldTy, RecordDecl, BS.getBeginLoc());
2492  }
2493  LastParamIndex = ParamIndex;
2494  return true;
2495  }
2496 
2497  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2498  return handleSpecialType(FD, FieldTy);
2499  }
2500 
2501  RecordDecl *wrapField(FieldDecl *Field, QualType FieldTy) {
2502  RecordDecl *WrapperClass =
2503  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().buildImplicitRecord("__wrapper_class");
2504  WrapperClass->startDefinition();
2505  Field = FieldDecl::Create(
2506  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), WrapperClass, SourceLocation(),
2507  SourceLocation(), /*Id=*/nullptr, FieldTy,
2508  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(FieldTy,
2509  SourceLocation()),
2510  /*BW=*/nullptr, /*Mutable=*/false, /*InitStyle=*/ICIS_NoInit);
2511  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
2512  WrapperClass->addDecl(Field);
2513  WrapperClass->completeDefinition();
2514  return WrapperClass;
2515  };
2516 
2517  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2518  QualType ModTy = ModifyAddressSpace(SemaSYCLRef, FieldTy);
2519  // When the kernel is generated, struct type kernel arguments are
2520  // decomposed; i.e. the parameters of the kernel are the fields of the
2521  // struct, and not the struct itself. This causes an error in the backend
2522  // when the struct field is a pointer, since non-USM pointers cannot be
2523  // passed directly. To work around this issue, all pointers inside the
2524  // struct are wrapped in a generated '__wrapper_class'.
2525  if (StructDepth) {
2526  RecordDecl *WrappedPointer = wrapField(FD, ModTy);
2527  ModTy = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getRecordType(WrappedPointer);
2528  }
2529 
2530  addParam(FD, ModTy);
2531  return true;
2532  }
2533 
2534  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2535  QualType ArrayTy = FieldTy;
2536 
2537  // This is an array of pointers or an array of a type with pointer.
2538  if (FD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
2539  ArrayTy = GenerateNewArrayType(FD, FieldTy);
2540 
2541  // Arrays are wrapped in a struct since they cannot be passed directly.
2542  RecordDecl *WrappedArray = wrapField(FD, ArrayTy);
2543  addParam(FD, SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getRecordType(WrappedArray));
2544  return true;
2545  }
2546 
2547  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2548  addParam(FD, FieldTy);
2549  return true;
2550  }
2551 
2552  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, FieldDecl *FD,
2553  QualType Ty) final {
2554  // This is a field which should not be decomposed.
2555  CXXRecordDecl *FieldRecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2556  assert(FieldRecordDecl && "Type must be a C++ record type");
2557  // Check if we need to generate a new type for this record,
2558  // i.e. this record contains pointers.
2559  if (FieldRecordDecl->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
2560  addParam(FD, GenerateNewRecordType(FieldRecordDecl));
2561  else
2562  addParam(FD, Ty);
2563  return true;
2564  }
2565 
2566  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *Base,
2567  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) final {
2568  // This is a base class which should not be decomposed.
2569  CXXRecordDecl *BaseRecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2570  assert(BaseRecordDecl && "Type must be a C++ record type");
2571  // Check if we need to generate a new type for this record,
2572  // i.e. this record contains pointers.
2573  if (BaseRecordDecl->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
2574  addParam(BS, GenerateNewRecordType(BaseRecordDecl));
2575  else
2576  addParam(BS, Ty);
2577  return true;
2578  }
2579 
2580  bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2581  return handleScalarType(FD, FieldTy);
2582  }

2585  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType() {
2586  ASTContext &Context = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
2587  StringRef Name = "_arg__specialization_constants_buffer";
2588  addParam(Name, Context.getPointerType(Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(
2589  Context.CharTy, LangAS::sycl_global)));
2590  }

2592  void setBody(CompoundStmt *KB) { KernelDecl->setBody(KB); }
2593 
2594  FunctionDecl *getKernelDecl() { return KernelDecl; }
2595 
2596  llvm::ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField() {
2597  return ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *>(std::begin(Params) + LastParamIndex,
2598  std::end(Params));
2599  }
2600 };
2601 
2602 // This Visitor traverses the AST of the function with
2603 // `sycl_kernel` attribute and returns the version of “operator()()” that is
2604 // called by KernelFunc. There will only be one call to KernelFunc in that
2605 // AST because the DPC++ headers are structured such that the user’s
2606 // kernel function is only called once. This ensures that the correct
2607 // “operator()()” function call is returned, when a named function object used
2608 // to define a kernel has more than one “operator()()” calls defined in it. For
2609 // example, in the code below, 'operator()(sycl::id<1> id)' is returned based on
2610 // the 'parallel_for' invocation which takes a 'sycl::range<1>(16)' argument.
2611 // class MyKernel {
2612 // public:
2613 // void operator()() const {
2614 // // code
2615 // }
2616 //
2617 // [[intel::reqd_sub_group_size(4)]] void operator()(sycl::id<1> id) const
2618 // {
2619 // // code
2620 // }
2621 // };
2622 //
2623 // int main() {
2624 //
2625 // Q.submit([&](sycl::handler& cgh) {
2626 // MyKernel kernelFunctorObject;
2627 // cgh.parallel_for(sycl::range<1>(16), kernelFunctorObject);
2628 // });
2629 // return 0;
2630 // }
2631 
2632 class KernelCallOperatorVisitor
2633  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<KernelCallOperatorVisitor> {
2634 
2635  FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc;
2636 
2637 public:
2638  CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator = nullptr;
2639  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj;
2640 
2641  KernelCallOperatorVisitor(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc,
2642  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj)
2643  : KernelCallerFunc(KernelCallerFunc), KernelObj(KernelObj) {}
2644 
2645  bool VisitCallExpr(CallExpr *CE) {
2646  Decl *CalleeDecl = CE->getCalleeDecl();
2647  if (isa_and_nonnull<CXXMethodDecl>(CalleeDecl)) {
2648  CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CalleeDecl);
2649  if (MD->getOverloadedOperator() == OO_Call &&
2650  MD->getParent() == KernelObj) {
2651  CallOperator = MD;
2652  }
2653  }
2654  return true;
2655  }
2656 
2657  CXXMethodDecl *getCallOperator() {
2658  if (CallOperator)
2659  return CallOperator;
2660 
2661  TraverseDecl(KernelCallerFunc);
2662  return CallOperator;
2663  }
2664 };

2777 class SyclOptReportCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {

2781  void addParam(const FieldDecl *KernelArg, QualType KernelArgType,
2782  StringRef KernelArgDescription,
2783  bool IsCompilerGeneratedType = false) {
2784  StringRef NameToEmitInDescription = KernelArg->getName();
2785  const RecordDecl *KernelArgParent = KernelArg->getParent();
2786  if (KernelArgParent && KernelArgDescription == "decomposed struct/class")
2787  NameToEmitInDescription = KernelArgParent->getName();
2788 
2789  unsigned KernelArgSize = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()
2790  .getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType)
2791  .getQuantity();
2792 
2793  SemaSYCLRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2794  DC.getKernelDecl(), NameToEmitInDescription,
2795  IsCompilerGeneratedType ? "Compiler generated"
2796  : KernelArgType.getAsString(),
2797  KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2798  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription),
2799  (KernelArgDescription == "decomposed struct/class")
2800  ? ("Field:" + KernelArg->getName().str() + ", ")
2801  : "");
2802  }

2851  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2852  QualType FieldTy) final {
2853  std::string KernelArgDescription = "base class " + FieldTy.getAsString();
2854  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()) {
2855  QualType KernelArgType = Param->getType();
2856  unsigned KernelArgSize = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()
2857  .getTypeSizeInChars(KernelArgType)
2858  .getQuantity();
2859  SemaSYCLRef.getDiagnostics().getSYCLOptReport().AddKernelArgs(
2860  DC.getKernelDecl(), FieldTy.getAsString(),
2861  KernelArgType.getAsString(), KernelInvocationLoc, KernelArgSize,
2862  getKernelArgDesc(KernelArgDescription), "");
2863  }
2864  return true;
2865  }
2866 
2867  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2868  std::string KernelArgDescription = "";
2869  bool IsCompilerGeneratedType = false;
2870  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter = DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
2871  // Compiler generated openCL kernel argument for current pointer field
2872  // is not a pointer. This means we are processing a nested pointer and
2873  // the openCL kernel argument is of type __wrapper_class.
2874  if (!KernelParameter->getType()->isPointerType()) {
2875  KernelArgDescription = "nested pointer";
2876  IsCompilerGeneratedType = true;
2877  }
2878 
2879  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField())
2880  addParam(FD, Param->getType(), KernelArgDescription,
2881  IsCompilerGeneratedType);
2882  return true;
2883  }
2884 
2885  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {

2887  return true;
2888  }
2889 
2890  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
2891  // Simple arrays are always wrapped.
2892  for (const auto *Param : DC.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField())
2893  addParam(FD, Param->getType(), "array", /*IsCompilerGeneratedType*/ true);
2894  return true;
2895  }

2897  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD,

2900  assert(RD && "Type must be a C++ record type");
2901  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
2902  addParam(FD, Ty, "object with pointer", /*IsCompilerGeneratedType*/ true);
2903  else
2904  addParam(FD, Ty);
2905  return true;
2906  }
2907 
2908  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
2909  QualType Ty) final {

2912  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
2913  addParam(BS, Ty, "base class with pointer",
2914  /*IsCompilerGeneratedType*/ true);
2915  else
2916  addParam(BS, Ty, "base class");

2930 static bool isESIMDKernelType(CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator) {

2934 class SyclKernelBodyCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
2935  SyclKernelDeclCreator &DeclCreator;
2936  llvm::SmallVector<Stmt *, 16> BodyStmts;
2937  llvm::SmallVector<InitListExpr *, 16> CollectionInitExprs;
2938  llvm::SmallVector<Stmt *, 16> FinalizeStmts;
2939  // This collection contains the information required to add/remove information
2940  // about arrays as we enter them. The InitializedEntity component is
2941  // necessary for initializing child members. uin64_t is the index of the
2942  // current element being worked on, which is updated every time we visit
2943  // nextElement.
2944  llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<InitializedEntity, uint64_t>, 8> ArrayInfos;
2945  VarDecl *KernelObjClone;
2946  InitializedEntity VarEntity;
2947  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> MemberExprBases;
2948  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> ArrayParamBases;
2949  FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc;
2950  SourceLocation KernelCallerSrcLoc; // KernelCallerFunc source location.
2951  // Contains a count of how many containers we're in. This is used by the
2952  // pointer-struct-wrapping code to ensure that we don't try to wrap
2953  // top-level pointers.
2954  uint64_t StructDepth = 0;
2955  VarDecl *KernelHandlerClone = nullptr;
2956  bool IsESIMD = false;
2957  CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator = nullptr;
2958 
2959  Stmt *replaceWithLocalClone(ParmVarDecl *OriginalParam, VarDecl *LocalClone,
2960  Stmt *FunctionBody) {
2961  // DeclRefExpr with valid source location but with decl which is not marked
2962  // as used is invalid.
2963  LocalClone->setIsUsed();
2964  std::pair<DeclaratorDecl *, DeclaratorDecl *> MappingPair =
2965  std::make_pair(OriginalParam, LocalClone);
2966  KernelBodyTransform KBT(MappingPair, SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef);
2967  return KBT.TransformStmt(FunctionBody).get();
2968  }
2969 
2970  // Using the statements/init expressions that we've created, this generates
2971  // the kernel body compound stmt. CompoundStmt needs to know its number of
2972  // statements in advance to allocate it, so we cannot do this as we go along.
2973  CompoundStmt *createKernelBody() {
2974  // Push the Kernel function scope to ensure the scope isn't empty
2975  SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.PushFunctionScope();
2976 
2977  // Initialize kernel object local clone
2978  assert(CollectionInitExprs.size() == 1 &&
2979  "Should have been popped down to just the first one");
2980  KernelObjClone->setInit(CollectionInitExprs.back());
2981 
2982  // Replace references to the kernel object in kernel body, to use the
2983  // compiler generated local clone
2984  Stmt *NewBody =
2985  replaceWithLocalClone(KernelCallerFunc->getParamDecl(0), KernelObjClone,
2986  KernelCallerFunc->getBody());
2987 
2988  // If kernel_handler argument is passed by SYCL kernel, replace references
2989  // to this argument in kernel body, to use the compiler generated local
2990  // clone
2991  if (ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerParam =
2992  getSyclKernelHandlerArg(KernelCallerFunc))
2993  NewBody = replaceWithLocalClone(KernelHandlerParam, KernelHandlerClone,
2994  NewBody);
2995 
2996  // Use transformed body (with clones) as kernel body
2997  BodyStmts.push_back(NewBody);
2998 
2999  BodyStmts.insert(BodyStmts.end(), FinalizeStmts.begin(),
3000  FinalizeStmts.end());
3001 
3002  return CompoundStmt::Create(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), BodyStmts,
3003  FPOptionsOverride(), {}, {});
3004  }
3005 
3006  void annotateHierarchicalParallelismAPICalls() {
3007  // Is this a hierarchical parallelism kernel invocation?
3008  if (getKernelInvocationKind(KernelCallerFunc) != InvokeParallelForWorkGroup)
3009  return;
3010 
3011  // Mark kernel object with work-group scope attribute to avoid work-item
3012  // scope memory allocation.
3013  KernelObjClone->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(
3014  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkGroup));
3015 
3016  assert(CallOperator && "non callable object is passed as kernel obj");
3017  // Mark the function that it "works" in a work group scope:
3018  // NOTE: In case of wait_for the marker call itself is
3019  // marked with work item scope attribute, here the '()' operator of the
3020  // object passed as parameter is marked. This is an optimization -
3021  // there are a lot of locals created at parallel_for_work_group
3022  // scope before calling the lambda - it is more efficient to have
3023  // all of them in the private address space rather then sharing via
3024  // the local AS. See parallel_for_work_group implementation in the
3025  // SYCL headers.
3026  if (!CallOperator->hasAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>()) {
3027  CallOperator->addAttr(SYCLScopeAttr::CreateImplicit(
3028  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), SYCLScopeAttr::Level::WorkGroup));
3029  // Search and mark wait_for calls:
3030  MarkWIScopeFnVisitor MarkWIScope(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext());
3031  MarkWIScope.TraverseDecl(CallOperator);
3032  // Now mark local variables declared in the PFWG lambda with work group
3033  // scope attribute
3034  addScopeAttrToLocalVars(*CallOperator);
3035  }
3036  }
3037 
3038  // Creates a DeclRefExpr to the ParmVar that represents the current field.
3039  Expr *createParamReferenceExpr() {
3040  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
3041  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
3042 
3043  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
3044  Expr *DRE = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(
3045  KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3046  return DRE;
3047  }
3048 
3049  // Creates a DeclRefExpr to the ParmVar that represents the current pointer
3050  // field.
3051  Expr *createPointerParamReferenceExpr(QualType PointerTy, bool Wrapped) {
3052  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
3053  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
3054 
3055  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
3056  Expr *DRE = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(
3057  KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3058 
3059  // Struct Type kernel arguments are decomposed. The pointer fields are
3060  // then wrapped inside a compiler generated struct. Therefore when
3061  // generating the initializers, we have to 'unwrap' the pointer.
3062  if (Wrapped) {
3063  CXXRecordDecl *WrapperStruct = ParamType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3064  // Pointer field wrapped inside __wrapper_class
3065  FieldDecl *Pointer = *(WrapperStruct->field_begin());
3066  DRE = buildMemberExpr(DRE, Pointer);
3067  ParamType = Pointer->getType();
3068  }
3069 
3070  DRE = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), ParamType,
3071  CK_LValueToRValue, DRE, /*BasePath=*/nullptr,
3072  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
3073 
3074  if (PointerTy->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
3075  ParamType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace())
3076  DRE = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), PointerTy,
3077  CK_AddressSpaceConversion, DRE, nullptr,
3078  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
3079 
3080  return DRE;
3081  }
3082 
3083  Expr *createSimpleArrayParamReferenceExpr(QualType ArrayTy) {
3084  ParmVarDecl *KernelParameter =
3085  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField()[0];
3086  QualType ParamType = KernelParameter->getOriginalType();
3087  Expr *DRE = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(
3088  KernelParameter, ParamType, VK_LValue, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3089 
3090  // Unwrap the array.
3091  CXXRecordDecl *WrapperStruct = ParamType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3092  FieldDecl *ArrayField = *(WrapperStruct->field_begin());
3093  return buildMemberExpr(DRE, ArrayField);
3094  }

3097  // field, returns a normal member initializer, if we're in a sub-array of a MD
3098  // array, returns an element initializer.

3100  if (isArrayElement(FD, Ty))
3101  return InitializedEntity::InitializeElement(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(),
3102  ArrayInfos.back().second,
3103  ArrayInfos.back().first);
3104  return InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(FD, &VarEntity);
3105  }

3207  void handleGeneratedType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
3208  // Equivalent of the following code is generated here:

3212

3240  /*HadMultipleCandidates*/ false,

3256  void createSpecialMethodCall(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, StringRef MethodName,
3257  SmallVectorImpl<Stmt *> &AddTo) {
3258  CXXMethodDecl *Method = getMethodByName(RD, MethodName);
3259  if (!Method)
3260  return;
3261 
3262  unsigned NumParams = Method->getNumParams();
3263  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ParamDREs(NumParams);
3264  llvm::ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> KernelParameters =
3265  DeclCreator.getParamVarDeclsForCurrentField();
3266  for (size_t I = 0; I < NumParams; ++I) {
3267  QualType ParamType = KernelParameters[I]->getOriginalType();
3268  ParamDREs[I] = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.BuildDeclRefExpr(
3269  KernelParameters[I], ParamType, VK_LValue, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3270  }
3271 
3272  MemberExpr *MethodME = buildMemberExpr(MemberExprBases.back(), Method);
3273 
3274  QualType ResultTy = Method->getReturnType();
3275  ExprValueKind VK = Expr::getValueKindForType(ResultTy);
3276  ResultTy = ResultTy.getNonLValueExprType(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext());
3277  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ParamStmts;
3278  const auto *Proto = cast<FunctionProtoType>(Method->getType());
3279  SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.GatherArgumentsForCall(KernelCallerSrcLoc, Method,
3280  Proto, 0, ParamDREs, ParamStmts);
3281  // [kernel_obj or wrapper object].accessor.__init(_ValueType*,
3282  // range<int>, range<int>, id<int>)
3283  AddTo.push_back(CXXMemberCallExpr::Create(
3284  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), MethodME, ParamStmts, ResultTy, VK,
3285  KernelCallerSrcLoc, FPOptionsOverride()));
3286  }

3326  static VarDecl *createKernelObjClone(ASTContext &Ctx, DeclContext *DC,
3327  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj) {
3328  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo =
3329  KernelObj->isLambda() ? KernelObj->getLambdaTypeInfo() : nullptr;
3330  IdentifierInfo *Ident = KernelObj->getIdentifier();
3331  if (!Ident)
3332  Ident = &Ctx.Idents.get("__SYCLKernel");
3333 
3334  VarDecl *VD = VarDecl::Create(
3335  Ctx, DC, KernelObj->getLocation(), KernelObj->getLocation(), Ident,
3336  QualType(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl(), 0), TSInfo, SC_None);
3337  return VD;
3338  }

3340  const llvm::StringLiteral getInitMethodName() const {
3341  return IsESIMD ? InitESIMDMethodName : InitMethodName;
3342  }

3344  // Default inits the type, then calls the init-method in the body.
3345  bool handleSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) {
3346  addFieldInit(FD, Ty, std::nullopt,
3347  InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc));
3348 
3349  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
3350 
3351  const auto *RecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3352  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, getInitMethodName(), BodyStmts);
3353  CXXMethodDecl *FinalizeMethod =
3354  getMethodByName(RecordDecl, FinalizeMethodName);
3355  // A finalize-method is expected for special type such as stream.
3356  if (FinalizeMethod)
3357  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, FinalizeMethodName, FinalizeStmts);
3358 
3359  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
3360 
3361  return true;
3362  }

3365  const auto *RecordDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3366  addBaseInit(BS, Ty, InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc));
3367  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, getInitMethodName(), BodyStmts);
3368  return true;
3369  }

3371  // Generate __init call for kernel handler argument
3372  void handleSpecialType(QualType KernelHandlerTy) {
3373  DeclRefExpr *KernelHandlerCloneRef = DeclRefExpr::Create(
3374  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), NestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
3375  KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelHandlerClone, false, DeclarationNameInfo(),
3376  KernelHandlerTy, VK_LValue);
3377  const auto *RecordDecl =
3378  KernelHandlerClone->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3379  MemberExprBases.push_back(KernelHandlerCloneRef);
3380  createSpecialMethodCall(RecordDecl, InitSpecConstantsBuffer, BodyStmts);
3381  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3382  }
3383 
3384  void createKernelHandlerClone(ASTContext &Ctx, DeclContext *DC,
3385  ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg) {
3386  QualType Ty = KernelHandlerArg->getType();
3387  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = Ctx.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty);
3388  KernelHandlerClone =
3389  VarDecl::Create(Ctx, DC, KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc,
3390  KernelHandlerArg->getIdentifier(), Ty, TSInfo, SC_None);
3391 
3392  // Default initialize clone
3393  InitializedEntity VarEntity =
3394  InitializedEntity::InitializeVariable(KernelHandlerClone);
3395  InitializationKind InitKind =
3396  InitializationKind::CreateDefault(KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3397  InitializationSequence InitSeq(SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef, VarEntity, InitKind,
3398  std::nullopt);
3399  ExprResult Init =
3400  InitSeq.Perform(SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef, VarEntity, InitKind, std::nullopt);
3401  KernelHandlerClone->setInit(
3402  SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Init.get()));
3403  KernelHandlerClone->setInitStyle(VarDecl::CallInit);
3404  }
3405 
3406  Expr *createArraySubscriptExpr(uint64_t Index, Expr *ArrayRef) {
3407  QualType SizeT = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getSizeType();
3408  llvm::APInt IndexVal{
3409  static_cast<unsigned>(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getTypeSize(SizeT)),
3410  Index, SizeT->isSignedIntegerType()};
3411  auto IndexLiteral = IntegerLiteral::Create(
3412  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), IndexVal, SizeT, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3413  ExprResult IndexExpr = SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(
3414  ArrayRef, KernelCallerSrcLoc, IndexLiteral, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3415  assert(!IndexExpr.isInvalid());
3416  return IndexExpr.get();
3417  }
3418 
3419  void addSimpleArrayInit(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
3420  Expr *ArrayRef = createSimpleArrayParamReferenceExpr(FieldTy);
3421  InitializationKind InitKind = InitializationKind::CreateDirect({}, {}, {});
3422 
3423  InitializedEntity Entity =
3424  InitializedEntity::InitializeMember(FD, &VarEntity, /*Implicit*/ true);
3425 
3426  addFieldInit(FD, FieldTy, ArrayRef, InitKind, Entity);
3427  }
3428 
3429  void addArrayElementInit(FieldDecl *FD, QualType T) {
3430  Expr *RCE = createReinterpretCastExpr(
3431  createGetAddressOf(ArrayParamBases.pop_back_val()),
3432  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getPointerType(T));
3433  Expr *Initializer = createDerefOp(RCE);
3434  addFieldInit(FD, T, Initializer);
3435  }
3436 
3437  // This function is recursive in order to handle
3438  // multi-dimensional arrays. If the array element is
3439  // an array, it implies that the array is multi-dimensional.
3440  // We continue recursion till we reach a non-array element to
3441  // generate required array subscript expressions.
3442  void createArrayInit(FieldDecl *FD, QualType T) {
3443  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
3444  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(T);
3445 
3446  if (!CAT) {
3447  addArrayElementInit(FD, T);
3448  return;
3449  }
3450 
3451  QualType ET = CAT->getElementType();
3452  uint64_t ElemCount = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
3453  enterArray(FD, T, ET);
3454 
3455  for (uint64_t Index = 0; Index < ElemCount; ++Index) {
3456  ArrayInfos.back().second = Index;
3457  Expr *ArraySubscriptExpr =
3458  createArraySubscriptExpr(Index, ArrayParamBases.back());
3459  ArrayParamBases.push_back(ArraySubscriptExpr);
3460  createArrayInit(FD, ET);
3461  }
3462 
3463  leaveArray(FD, T, ET);
3464  }
3465 
3466  // This function is used to create initializers for a top
3467  // level array which contains pointers. The openCl kernel
3468  // parameter for this array will be a wrapper class
3469  // which contains the generated type. This function generates
3470  // code equivalent to:
3471  // void ocl_kernel(__wrapper_class WrappedGT) {
3472  // Kernel KernelObjClone {
3473  // *reinterpret_cast<UserArrayET*>(&WrappedGT.GeneratedArr[0]),
3474  // *reinterpret_cast<UserArrayET*>(&WrappedGT.GeneratedArr[1]),
3475  // *reinterpret_cast<UserArrayET*>(&WrappedGT.GeneratedArr[2])
3476  // };
3477  // }
3478  void handleGeneratedArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) {
3479  ArrayParamBases.push_back(createSimpleArrayParamReferenceExpr(FieldTy));
3480  createArrayInit(FD, FieldTy);
3481  }
3482 
3483 public:
3484  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
3485  SyclKernelBodyCreator(SemaSYCL &S, SyclKernelDeclCreator &DC,
3486  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj,
3487  FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc, bool IsSIMDKernel,
3488  CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator)
3489  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), DeclCreator(DC),
3490  KernelObjClone(createKernelObjClone(S.getASTContext(),
3491  DC.getKernelDecl(), KernelObj)),
3492  VarEntity(InitializedEntity::InitializeVariable(KernelObjClone)),
3493  KernelCallerFunc(KernelCallerFunc),
3494  KernelCallerSrcLoc(KernelCallerFunc->getLocation()),
3495  IsESIMD(IsSIMDKernel), CallOperator(CallOperator) {
3496  CollectionInitExprs.push_back(createInitListExpr(KernelObj));
3497  annotateHierarchicalParallelismAPICalls();
3498 
3499  Stmt *DS = new (S.getASTContext()) DeclStmt(
3500  DeclGroupRef(KernelObjClone), KernelCallerSrcLoc, KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3501  BodyStmts.push_back(DS);
3502  DeclRefExpr *KernelObjCloneRef = DeclRefExpr::Create(
3503  S.getASTContext(), NestedNameSpecifierLoc(), KernelCallerSrcLoc,
3504  KernelObjClone, false, DeclarationNameInfo(),
3505  QualType(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl(), 0), VK_LValue);
3506  MemberExprBases.push_back(KernelObjCloneRef);
3507  }
3508 
3509  ~SyclKernelBodyCreator() {
3510  CompoundStmt *KernelBody = createKernelBody();
3511  DeclCreator.setBody(KernelBody);
3512  }
3513 
3514  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
3515  return handleSpecialType(FD, Ty);
3516  }
3517 
3518  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3519  QualType Ty) final {
3520  return handleSpecialType(BS, Ty);
3521  }
3522 
3523  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3524  Expr *PointerRef =
3525  createPointerParamReferenceExpr(FieldTy, StructDepth != 0);
3526  addFieldInit(FD, FieldTy, PointerRef);
3527  return true;
3528  }
3529 
3530  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3531  if (FD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
3532  handleGeneratedArrayType(FD, FieldTy);
3533  else
3534  addSimpleArrayInit(FD, FieldTy);
3535  return true;
3536  }
3537 
3538  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD,
3539  QualType Ty) final {
3540  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3541  assert(RD && "Type must be a C++ record type");
3542  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
3543  handleGeneratedType(FD, Ty);
3544  else
3545  addSimpleFieldInit(FD, Ty);
3546  return true;
3547  }
3548 
3549  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3550  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS, QualType Ty) final {
3551  CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3552  assert(BaseDecl && "Type must be a C++ record type");
3553  if (BaseDecl->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
3554  handleGeneratedType(RD, BS, Ty);
3555  else
3556  addSimpleBaseInit(BS, Ty);
3557  return true;
3558  }
3559 
3560  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3561  addSimpleFieldInit(FD, FieldTy);
3562  return true;
3563  }
3564 
3565  bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3566  addSimpleFieldInit(FD, FieldTy);
3567  return true;
3568  }
3569 
3570  // Default inits the type, then calls the init-method in the body
3571  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType(ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg) {
3572 
3573  // Create and default initialize local clone of kernel handler
3574  createKernelHandlerClone(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(),
3575  DeclCreator.getKernelDecl(), KernelHandlerArg);
3576 
3577  // Add declaration statement to openCL kernel body
3578  Stmt *DS = new (SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext())
3579  DeclStmt(DeclGroupRef(KernelHandlerClone), KernelCallerSrcLoc,
3580  KernelCallerSrcLoc);
3581  BodyStmts.push_back(DS);
3582 
3583  // Generate
3584  // KernelHandlerClone.__init_specialization_constants_buffer(specialization_constants_buffer)
3585  // call if target does not have native support for specialization constants.
3586  // Here, specialization_constants_buffer is the compiler generated kernel
3587  // argument of type char*.
3588  if (!isDefaultSPIRArch(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()))
3589  handleSpecialType(KernelHandlerArg->getType());
3590  }
3591 
3592  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
3593  ++StructDepth;
3594  addCollectionInitListExpr(Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3595 
3596  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
3597  return true;
3598  }
3599 
3600  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
3601  --StructDepth;
3602  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
3603 
3604  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, Ty);
3605  return true;
3606  }
3607 
3608  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3609  QualType) final {
3610  ++StructDepth;
3611 
3612  CXXCastPath BasePath;
3613  QualType DerivedTy(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
3614  QualType BaseTy = BS.getType();
3615  SemaSYCLRef.SemaRef.CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
3616  DerivedTy, BaseTy, KernelCallerSrcLoc, SourceRange(), &BasePath,
3617  /*IgnoreBaseAccess*/ true);
3618  auto Cast = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
3619  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), BaseTy, CK_DerivedToBase,
3620  MemberExprBases.back(),
3621  /* CXXCastPath=*/&BasePath, VK_LValue, FPOptionsOverride());
3622  MemberExprBases.push_back(Cast);
3623  addCollectionInitListExpr(BaseTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3624  return true;
3625  }
3626 
3627  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3628  QualType) final {
3629  --StructDepth;
3630  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3631  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
3632  return true;
3633  }
3634 
3635  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayType,
3636  QualType ElementType) final {
3637  const ConstantArrayType *CAT =
3638  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getAsConstantArrayType(ArrayType);
3639  assert(CAT && "Should only be called on constant-size array.");
3640  uint64_t ArraySize = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
3641  addCollectionInitListExpr(ArrayType, ArraySize);
3642  ArrayInfos.emplace_back(getFieldEntity(FD, ArrayType), 0);
3643 
3644  // If this is the top-level array, we need to make a MemberExpr in addition
3645  // to an array subscript.
3646  addFieldMemberExpr(FD, ArrayType);
3647  return true;
3648  }
3649 
3650  bool nextElement(QualType, uint64_t Index) final {
3651  ArrayInfos.back().second = Index;
3652 
3653  // Pop off the last member expr base.
3654  if (Index != 0)
3655  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3656 
3657  MemberExprBases.push_back(
3658  createArraySubscriptExpr(Index, MemberExprBases.back()));
3659  return true;
3660  }
3661 
3662  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayType,
3663  QualType ElementType) final {
3664  CollectionInitExprs.pop_back();
3665  ArrayInfos.pop_back();
3666 
3667  // Remove the IndexExpr.
3668  if (!FD->hasAttr<SYCLGenerateNewTypeAttr>())
3669  MemberExprBases.pop_back();
3670  else
3671  ArrayParamBases.pop_back();
3672 
3673  // Remove the field access expr as well.
3674  removeFieldMemberExpr(FD, ArrayType);
3675  return true;
3676  }
3677 };
3678 
3679 // Kernels are only the unnamed-lambda feature if the feature is enabled, AND
3680 // the first template argument has been corrected by the library to match the
3681 // functor type.
3682 static bool IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(SemaSYCL &SemaSYCLRef, const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3683  if (!SemaSYCLRef.getLangOpts().SYCLUnnamedLambda)
3684  return false;
3685  QualType FunctorTy = GetSYCLKernelObjectType(FD);
3686  QualType TmplArgTy = calculateKernelNameType(SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext(), FD);
3687  return SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().hasSameType(FunctorTy, TmplArgTy);
3688 }

3690 class SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator : public SyclKernelFieldHandler {
3691  SYCLIntegrationHeader &Header;
3692  int64_t CurOffset = 0;
3693  llvm::SmallVector<size_t, 16> ArrayBaseOffsets;
3694  int StructDepth = 0;
3695 
3696  // A series of functions to calculate the change in offset based on the type.
3697  int64_t offsetOf(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArgTy) const {
3698  return isArrayElement(FD, ArgTy)
3699  ? 0
3700  : SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getFieldOffset(FD) / 8;
3701  }
3702 
3703  int64_t offsetOf(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXRecordDecl *Base) const {
3704  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
3705  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3706  return Layout.getBaseClassOffset(Base).getQuantity();
3707  }
3708 
3709  void addParam(const FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArgTy,
3710  SYCLIntegrationHeader::kernel_param_kind_t Kind) {
3711  addParam(ArgTy, Kind, offsetOf(FD, ArgTy));
3712  }
3713  void addParam(QualType ArgTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kernel_param_kind_t Kind,
3714  uint64_t OffsetAdj) {
3715  uint64_t Size;
3716  Size = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ArgTy).getQuantity();
3717  Header.addParamDesc(Kind, static_cast<unsigned>(Size),
3718  static_cast<unsigned>(CurOffset + OffsetAdj));
3719  }
3720 
3721 public:
3722  static constexpr const bool VisitInsideSimpleContainers = false;
3723  SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator(bool IsESIMD, SemaSYCL &S,
3724  SYCLIntegrationHeader &H,
3725  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj, QualType NameType,
3726  FunctionDecl *KernelFunc)
3727  : SyclKernelFieldHandler(S), Header(H) {
3728 
3729  // The header needs to access the kernel object size.
3730  int64_t ObjSize = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext()
3731  .getTypeSizeInChars(KernelObj->getTypeForDecl())
3732  .getQuantity();
3733  Header.startKernel(KernelFunc, NameType, KernelObj->getLocation(), IsESIMD,
3734  IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(S, KernelFunc), ObjSize);
3735  }
3736 
3737  bool handleSyclSpecialType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3738  const CXXBaseSpecifier &BC,
3739  QualType FieldTy) final {
3740  const auto *AccTy =
3741  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl());
3742  assert(AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() >= 2 &&
3743  "Incorrect template args for Accessor Type");
3744  int Dims = static_cast<int>(
3745  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[1].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
3746  int Info = getAccessTarget(FieldTy, AccTy) | (Dims << 11);
3747  Header.addParamDesc(SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_accessor, Info,
3748  CurOffset +
3749  offsetOf(RD, BC.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()));
3750  return true;
3751  }
3752 
3753  bool handleSyclSpecialType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3754  const auto *ClassTy = FieldTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3755  assert(ClassTy && "Type must be a C++ record type");
3756  if (isSyclAccessorType(FieldTy)) {
3757  const auto *AccTy =
3758  cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(FieldTy->getAsRecordDecl());
3759  assert(AccTy->getTemplateArgs().size() >= 2 &&
3760  "Incorrect template args for Accessor Type");
3761  int Dims = static_cast<int>(
3762  AccTy->getTemplateArgs()[1].getAsIntegral().getExtValue());
3763  int Info = getAccessTarget(FieldTy, AccTy) | (Dims << 11);
3764 
3765  Header.addParamDesc(SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_accessor, Info,
3766  CurOffset + offsetOf(FD, FieldTy));
3767  } else if (SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::stream)) {
3768  addParam(FD, FieldTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_stream);
3769  } else if (SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::sampler) ||
3770  SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::annotated_ptr) ||
3771  SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::annotated_arg)) {
3772  CXXMethodDecl *InitMethod = getMethodByName(ClassTy, InitMethodName);
3773  assert(InitMethod && "type must have __init method");
3774  const ParmVarDecl *InitArg = InitMethod->getParamDecl(0);
3775  assert(InitArg && "Init method must have arguments");
3776  QualType T = InitArg->getType();
3777  SYCLIntegrationHeader::kernel_param_kind_t ParamKind =
3778  SemaSYCL::isSyclType(FieldTy, SYCLTypeAttr::sampler)
3779  ? SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_sampler
3780  : (T->isPointerType() ? SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_pointer
3781  : SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout);
3782  addParam(T, ParamKind, offsetOf(FD, FieldTy));
3783  } else {
3784  llvm_unreachable(
3785  "Unexpected SYCL special class when generating integration header");
3786  }
3787  return true;
3788  }
3789 
3790  bool handlePointerType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3791  addParam(FD, FieldTy,
3792  ((StructDepth) ? SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout
3793  : SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_pointer));
3794  return true;
3795  }
3796 
3797  bool handleScalarType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3798  addParam(FD, FieldTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout);
3799  return true;
3800  }
3801 
3802  bool handleSimpleArrayType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3803  // Arrays are always wrapped inside of structs, so just treat it as a simple
3804  // struct.
3805  addParam(FD, FieldTy, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout);
3806  return true;
3807  }
3808 
3809  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD,
3810  QualType Ty) final {
3811  addParam(FD, Ty, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout);
3812  return true;
3813  }
3814 
3815  bool handleNonDecompStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *Base,
3816  const CXXBaseSpecifier &, QualType Ty) final {
3817  addParam(Ty, SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_std_layout,
3818  offsetOf(Base, Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()));
3819  return true;
3820  }
3821 
3822  bool handleUnionType(FieldDecl *FD, QualType FieldTy) final {
3823  return handleScalarType(FD, FieldTy);
3824  }
3825 
3826  void handleSyclKernelHandlerType(QualType Ty) {
3827  // The compiler generated kernel argument used to initialize SYCL 2020
3828  // specialization constants, `specialization_constants_buffer`, should
3829  // have corresponding entry in integration header.
3830  ASTContext &Context = SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext();
3831  // Offset is zero since kernel_handler argument is not part of
3832  // kernel object (i.e. it is not captured)
3833  addParam(Context.getPointerType(Context.CharTy),
3834  SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_specialization_constants_buffer, 0);
3835  }
3836 
3837  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
3838  ++StructDepth;
3839  CurOffset += offsetOf(FD, Ty);
3840  return true;
3841  }
3842 
3843  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *, FieldDecl *FD, QualType Ty) final {
3844  --StructDepth;
3845  CurOffset -= offsetOf(FD, Ty);
3846  return true;
3847  }
3848 
3849  bool enterStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3850  QualType) final {
3851  CurOffset += offsetOf(RD, BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3852  return true;
3853  }
3854 
3855  bool leaveStruct(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS,
3856  QualType) final {
3857  CurOffset -= offsetOf(RD, BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3858  return true;
3859  }
3860 
3861  bool enterArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType) final {
3862  ArrayBaseOffsets.push_back(CurOffset + offsetOf(FD, ArrayTy));
3863  return true;
3864  }
3865 
3866  bool nextElement(QualType ET, uint64_t Index) final {
3867  int64_t Size =
3868  SemaSYCLRef.getASTContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ET).getQuantity();
3869  CurOffset = ArrayBaseOffsets.back() + Size * Index;
3870  return true;
3871  }
3872 
3873  bool leaveArray(FieldDecl *FD, QualType ArrayTy, QualType) final {
3874  CurOffset = ArrayBaseOffsets.pop_back_val();
3875  CurOffset -= offsetOf(FD, ArrayTy);
3876  return true;
3877  }
3878 
3879  using SyclKernelFieldHandler::enterStruct;
3880  using SyclKernelFieldHandler::leaveStruct;
3881 };
