3895 class SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor
3896  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>,
3897  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor> {
3898  SemaSYCL &S;
3899  SourceLocation KernelInvocationFuncLoc;
3900  QualType KernelNameType;
3901  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>;
3902  using InnerTemplArgVisitor =
3903  ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor>;
3904  bool IsInvalid = false;
3905  bool IsUnnamedKernel = false;
3906 
3907  void VisitTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
3908  for (auto &A : Args)
3909  Visit(A);
3910  }
3911 
3912 public:
3913  SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor(SemaSYCL &S, SourceLocation KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3914  QualType KernelNameType, bool IsUnnamedKernel)
3915  : S(S), KernelInvocationFuncLoc(KernelInvocationFuncLoc),
3916  KernelNameType(KernelNameType), IsUnnamedKernel(IsUnnamedKernel) {}
3917 
3918  bool isValid() { return !IsInvalid; }
3919 
3920  void Visit(QualType T) {
3921  if (T.isNull())
3922  return;
3923 
3924  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3925  // If KernelNameType has template args visit each template arg via
3926  // ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor
3927  if (const auto *TSD =
3928  dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
3929  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
3930 
3931  VisitTemplateArgs(Args);
3932  } else {
3933  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(T.getTypePtr());
3934  }
3935  }
3936 
3937  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
3938  if (TA.isNull())
3939  return;
3940  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
3941  }
3942 
3943  void VisitBuiltinType(const BuiltinType *TT) {
3944  if (TT->isNullPtrType()) {
3945  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::err_nullptr_t_type_in_sycl_kernel)
3946  << KernelNameType;
3947 
3948  IsInvalid = true;
3949  }
3950  return;
3951  }
3952 
3953  void VisitTagType(const TagType *TT) {
3954  return DiagnoseKernelNameType(TT->getDecl());
3955  }
3956 
3957  void DiagnoseKernelNameType(const NamedDecl *DeclNamed) {
3958  /*
3959  This is a helper function which throws an error if the kernel name
3960  declaration is:
3961  * declared within namespace 'std' (at any level)
3962  e.g., namespace std { namespace literals { class Whatever; } }
3963  h.single_task<std::literals::Whatever>([]() {});
3964  * declared within a function
3965  e.g., void foo() { struct S { int i; };
3966  h.single_task<S>([]() {}); }
3967  * declared within another tag
3968  e.g., struct S { struct T { int i } t; };
3969  h.single_task<S::T>([]() {});
3970  */
3971 
3972  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(DeclNamed)) {
3973  if (!ED->isScoped() && !ED->isFixed()) {
3974  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
3975  << /* unscoped enum requires fixed underlying type */ 1
3976  << DeclNamed;
3977  IsInvalid = true;
3978  }
3979  }
3980 
3981  const DeclContext *DeclCtx = DeclNamed->getDeclContext();
3982  if (DeclCtx && !IsUnnamedKernel) {
3983 
3984  // Check if the kernel name declaration is declared within namespace
3985  // "std" (at any level).
3986  while (!DeclCtx->isTranslationUnit() && isa<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx)) {
3987  const auto *NSDecl = cast<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx);
3988  if (NSDecl->isStdNamespace()) {
3989  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
3990  diag::err_invalid_std_type_in_sycl_kernel)
3991  << KernelNameType << DeclNamed;
3992  IsInvalid = true;
3993  return;
3994  }
3995  DeclCtx = DeclCtx->getParent();
3996  }
3997 
3998  // Check if the kernel name is a Tag declaration
3999  // local to a non-namespace scope (i.e. Inside a function or within
4000  // another Tag etc).
4001  if (!DeclCtx->isTranslationUnit() && !isa<NamespaceDecl>(DeclCtx)) {
4002  if (const auto *Tag = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(DeclNamed)) {
4003  bool UnnamedLambdaUsed = Tag->getIdentifier() == nullptr;
4004 
4005  if (UnnamedLambdaUsed) {
4006  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
4007  diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
4008  << /* unnamed type is invalid */ 2 << KernelNameType;
4009  IsInvalid = true;
4010  return;
4011  }
4012 
4013  // Diagnose used types without complete definition i.e.
4014  // int main() {
4015  // class KernelName1;
4016  // parallel_for<class KernelName1>(..);
4017  // }
4018  // This case can only be diagnosed during host compilation because the
4019  // integration header is required to distinguish between the invalid
4020  // code (above) and the following valid code:
4021  // int main() {
4022  // parallel_for<class KernelName2>(..);
4023  // }
4024  // The device compiler forward declares both KernelName1 and
4025  // KernelName2 in the integration header as ::KernelName1 and
4026  // ::KernelName2. The problem with the former case is the additional
4027  // declaration 'class KernelName1' in non-global scope. Lookup in this
4028  // case will resolve to ::main::KernelName1 (instead of
4029  // ::KernelName1). Since this is not visible to runtime code that
4030  // submits kernels, this is invalid.
4031  if (Tag->isCompleteDefinition() ||
4032  S.getLangOpts().SYCLEnableIntHeaderDiags) {
4033  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc,
4034  diag::err_sycl_kernel_incorrectly_named)
4035  << /* kernel name should be forward declarable at namespace
4036  scope */
4037  0 << KernelNameType;
4038  IsInvalid = true;
4039  } else {
4040  S.Diag(KernelInvocationFuncLoc, diag::warn_sycl_implicit_decl);
4041  S.Diag(DeclNamed->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
4042  << DeclNamed->getName();
4043  }
4044  }
4045  }
4046  }
4047  }
4048 
4049  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4050  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
4051  if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
4052  VisitTagType(ET);
4053  else
4054  Visit(T);
4055  }
4056 
4057  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4058  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
4059  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
4060  VisitTagType(ET);
4061  }
4062 
4063  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4064  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
4065  assert(TD && "template declaration must be available");
4066  TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams = TD->getTemplateParameters();
4067  for (NamedDecl *P : *TemplateParams) {
4068  if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *TemplateParam =
4069  dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(P))
4070  if (const EnumType *ET = TemplateParam->getType()->getAs<EnumType>())
4071  VisitTagType(ET);
4072  }
4073  }
4074 
4075  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4076  VisitTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
4077  }
4078 };
4079 
4080 void SemaSYCL::CheckSYCLKernelCall(FunctionDecl *KernelFunc,
4081  ArrayRef<const Expr *> Args) {
4082  QualType KernelNameType =
4083  calculateKernelNameType(getASTContext(), KernelFunc);
4084  SYCLKernelNameTypeVisitor KernelNameTypeVisitor(
4085  *this, Args[0]->getExprLoc(), KernelNameType,
4086  IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(*this, KernelFunc));
4087  KernelNameTypeVisitor.Visit(KernelNameType.getCanonicalType());
4088 
4089  // FIXME: In place until the library works around its 'host' invocation
4090  // issues.
4091  if (!SemaRef.LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
4092  return;
4093 
4094  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj =
4095  GetSYCLKernelObjectType(KernelFunc)->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4096 
4097  if (!KernelObj || (KernelObj && !KernelObj->hasDefinition())) {
4098  Diag(Args[0]->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_kernel_not_function_object);
4099  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
4100  return;
4101  }
4102 
4103  if (KernelObj->isLambda()) {
4104  for (const LambdaCapture &LC : KernelObj->captures())
4105  if (LC.capturesThis() && LC.isImplicit()) {
4106  Diag(LC.getLocation(), diag::err_implicit_this_capture);
4107  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
4108  }
4109  }
4110 
4111  // check that calling kernel conforms to spec
4112  QualType KernelParamTy = KernelFunc->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
4113  if (KernelParamTy->isReferenceType()) {
4114  // passing by reference, so emit warning if not using SYCL 2020
4115  if (SemaRef.LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() < LangOptions::SYCL_2020)
4116  Diag(KernelFunc->getLocation(), diag::warn_sycl_pass_by_reference_future);
4117  } else {
4118  // passing by value. emit warning if using SYCL 2020 or greater
4119  if (SemaRef.LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() > LangOptions::SYCL_2017)
4120  Diag(KernelFunc->getLocation(), diag::warn_sycl_pass_by_value_deprecated);
4121  }
4122 
4123  // Do not visit invalid kernel object.
4124  if (KernelObj->isInvalidDecl())
4125  return;
4126 
4127  SyclKernelDecompMarker DecompMarker(*this);
4128  SyclKernelFieldChecker FieldChecker(*this);
4129  SyclKernelUnionChecker UnionChecker(*this);
4130 
4131  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{*this};
4132 
4133  DiagnosingSYCLKernel = true;
4134 
4135  // Emit diagnostics for SYCL device kernels only
4136  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, FieldChecker, UnionChecker, DecompMarker);
4137  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, FieldChecker, UnionChecker,
4138  DecompMarker);
4139 
4140  DiagnosingSYCLKernel = false;
4141  // Set the kernel function as invalid, if any of the checkers fail validation.
4142  if (!FieldChecker.isValid() || !UnionChecker.isValid() ||
4143  !KernelNameTypeVisitor.isValid())
4144  KernelFunc->setInvalidDecl();
4145 }
4146 
4147 // For a wrapped parallel_for, copy attributes from original
4148 // kernel to wrapped kernel.
4149 void SemaSYCL::copySYCLKernelAttrs(CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator) {
4150  // Get the operator() function of the wrapper.
4151  assert(CallOperator && "invalid kernel object");
4152 
4153  typedef std::pair<FunctionDecl *, FunctionDecl *> ChildParentPair;
4154  llvm::SmallPtrSet<FunctionDecl *, 16> Visited;
4155  llvm::SmallVector<ChildParentPair, 16> WorkList;
4156  WorkList.push_back({CallOperator, nullptr});
4157  FunctionDecl *KernelBody = nullptr;
4158 
4159  CallGraph SYCLCG;
4160  SYCLCG.addToCallGraph(CallOperator);
4161  while (!WorkList.empty()) {
4162  FunctionDecl *FD = WorkList.back().first;
4163  FunctionDecl *ParentFD = WorkList.back().second;
4164 
4165  if ((ParentFD == CallOperator) && isSYCLKernelBodyFunction(FD)) {
4166  KernelBody = FD;
4167  break;
4168  }
4169 
4170  WorkList.pop_back();
4171  if (!Visited.insert(FD).second)
4172  continue; // We've already seen this Decl
4173 
4174  CallGraphNode *N = SYCLCG.getNode(FD);
4175  if (!N)
4176  continue;
4177 
4178  for (const CallGraphNode *CI : *N) {
4179  if (auto *Callee = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CI->getDecl())) {
4180  Callee = Callee->getMostRecentDecl();
4181  if (!Visited.count(Callee))
4182  WorkList.push_back({Callee, FD});
4183  }
4184  }
4185  }
4186 
4187  assert(KernelBody && "improper parallel_for wrap");
4188  if (KernelBody) {
4189  llvm::SmallVector<Attr *, 4> Attrs;
4190  collectSYCLAttributes(*this, KernelBody, Attrs, /*DirectlyCalled*/ true);
4191  if (!Attrs.empty())
4192  llvm::for_each(Attrs,
4193  [CallOperator](Attr *A) { CallOperator->addAttr(A); });
4194  }
4195 }
4196 
4197 void SemaSYCL::SetSYCLKernelNames() {
4198  std::unique_ptr<MangleContext> MangleCtx(
4199  getASTContext().createMangleContext());
4200  // We assume the list of KernelDescs is the complete list of kernels needing
4201  // to be rewritten.
4202  for (const std::pair<const FunctionDecl *, FunctionDecl *> &Pair :
4203  SyclKernelsToOpenCLKernels) {
4204  std::string CalculatedName, StableName;
4205  std::tie(CalculatedName, StableName) =
4206  constructKernelName(*this, Pair.first, *MangleCtx);
4207  StringRef KernelName(
4208  IsSYCLUnnamedKernel(*this, Pair.first) ? StableName : CalculatedName);
4209 
4210  getSyclIntegrationHeader().updateKernelNames(Pair.first, KernelName,
4211  StableName);
4212 
4213  // Set name of generated kernel.
4214  Pair.second->setDeclName(&getASTContext().Idents.get(KernelName));
4215  // Update the AsmLabel for this generated kernel.
4216  Pair.second->addAttr(
4217  AsmLabelAttr::CreateImplicit(getASTContext(), KernelName));
4218  }
4219 }
4220 
4221 // Generates the OpenCL kernel using KernelCallerFunc (kernel caller
4222 // function) defined is SYCL headers.
4223 // Generated OpenCL kernel contains the body of the kernel caller function,
4224 // receives OpenCL like parameters and additionally does some manipulation to
4225 // initialize captured lambda/functor fields with these parameters.
4226 // SYCL runtime marks kernel caller function with sycl_kernel attribute.
4227 // To be able to generate OpenCL kernel from KernelCallerFunc we put
4228 // the following requirements to the function which SYCL runtime can mark with
4229 // sycl_kernel attribute:
4230 // - Must be template function with at least two template parameters.
4231 // First parameter must represent "unique kernel name"
4232 // Second parameter must be the function object type
4233 // - Must have only one function parameter - function object.
4234 //
4235 // Example of kernel caller function:
4236 // template <typename KernelName, typename KernelType/*, ...*/>
4237 // __attribute__((sycl_kernel)) void kernel_caller_function(KernelType
4238 // KernelFuncObj) {
4239 // KernelFuncObj();
4240 // }
4241 //
4242 //
4243 void SemaSYCL::ConstructOpenCLKernel(FunctionDecl *KernelCallerFunc,
4244  MangleContext &MC) {
4245  // The first argument to the KernelCallerFunc is the lambda object.
4246  const CXXRecordDecl *KernelObj =
4247  GetSYCLKernelObjectType(KernelCallerFunc)->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4248  assert(KernelObj && "invalid kernel caller");
4249 
4250  // Do not visit invalid kernel object.
4251  if (KernelObj->isInvalidDecl())
4252  return;
4253 
4254  KernelCallOperatorVisitor KernelCallOperator(KernelCallerFunc, KernelObj);
4255  CXXMethodDecl *CallOperator = nullptr;
4256 
4257  if (KernelObj->isLambda())
4258  CallOperator = KernelObj->getLambdaCallOperator();
4259  else
4260  CallOperator = KernelCallOperator.getCallOperator();
4261 
4262  {
4263  // Do enough to calculate the StableName for the purposes of the hackery
4264  // below for __pf_kernel_wrapper. Placed in a scope so that we don't
4265  // accidentially use these values below, before the names are stabililzed.
4266  std::string CalculatedName, StableName;
4267  std::tie(CalculatedName, StableName) =
4268  constructKernelName(*this, KernelCallerFunc, MC);
4269 
4270  // Attributes of a user-written SYCL kernel must be copied to the internally
4271  // generated alternative kernel, identified by a known string in its name.
4272  if (StableName.find("__pf_kernel_wrapper") != std::string::npos)
4273  copySYCLKernelAttrs(CallOperator);
4274  }
4275 
4276  bool IsSIMDKernel = isESIMDKernelType(CallOperator);
4277 
4278  SyclKernelArgsSizeChecker argsSizeChecker(*this, KernelObj->getLocation(),
4279  IsSIMDKernel);
4280  ESIMDKernelDiagnostics esimdKernel(*this, KernelObj->getLocation(),
4281  IsSIMDKernel);
4282 
4283  SyclKernelDeclCreator kernel_decl(*this, KernelObj->getLocation(),
4284  KernelCallerFunc->isInlined(), IsSIMDKernel,
4285  KernelCallerFunc);
4286  SyclKernelBodyCreator kernel_body(*this, kernel_decl, KernelObj,
4287  KernelCallerFunc, IsSIMDKernel,
4288  CallOperator);
4289  SyclKernelIntHeaderCreator int_header(
4290  IsSIMDKernel, *this, getSyclIntegrationHeader(), KernelObj,
4291  calculateKernelNameType(getASTContext(), KernelCallerFunc),
4292  KernelCallerFunc);
4293 
4294  SyclKernelIntFooterCreator int_footer(*this, getSyclIntegrationFooter());
4295  SyclOptReportCreator opt_report(*this, kernel_decl, KernelObj->getLocation());
4296 
4297  KernelObjVisitor Visitor{*this};
4298 
4299  // Visit handlers to generate information for optimization record only if
4300  // optimization record is saved.
4301  if (!getLangOpts().OptRecordFile.empty()) {
4302  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, argsSizeChecker, esimdKernel,
4303  kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header, int_footer,
4304  opt_report);
4305  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, argsSizeChecker, esimdKernel,
4306  kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header, int_footer,
4307  opt_report);
4308  } else {
4309  Visitor.VisitRecordBases(KernelObj, argsSizeChecker, esimdKernel,
4310  kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header, int_footer);
4311  Visitor.VisitRecordFields(KernelObj, argsSizeChecker, esimdKernel,
4312  kernel_decl, kernel_body, int_header, int_footer);
4313  }
4314 
4315  if (ParmVarDecl *KernelHandlerArg =
4316  getSyclKernelHandlerArg(KernelCallerFunc)) {
4317  kernel_decl.handleSyclKernelHandlerType();
4318  kernel_body.handleSyclKernelHandlerType(KernelHandlerArg);
4319  int_header.handleSyclKernelHandlerType(KernelHandlerArg->getType());
4320 
4321  if (!getLangOpts().OptRecordFile.empty())
4322  opt_report.handleSyclKernelHandlerType();
4323  }
4324 }
4325 
4326 // Figure out the sub-group for the this function. First we check the
4327 // attributes, then the global settings.
4328 static std::pair<LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType, int64_t>
4329 CalcEffectiveSubGroup(ASTContext &Ctx, const LangOptions &LO,
4330  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4331  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4332  int64_t Val = getIntExprValue(A->getValue(), Ctx);
4333  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Integer, Val};
4334  }
4335 
4336  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4337  if (A->getType() == IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr::Primary)
4338  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Primary, 0};
4339  return {LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Auto, 0};
4340  }
4341 
4342  // Return the global settings.
4343  return {LO.getDefaultSubGroupSizeType(),
4344  static_cast<uint64_t>(LO.DefaultSubGroupSize)};
4345 }
4346 
4347 static SourceLocation GetSubGroupLoc(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4348  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>())
4349  return A->getLocation();
4350  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
4351  return A->getLocation();
4352  return SourceLocation{};
4353 }
4354 
4355 static void CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(SemaSYCL &S, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel,
4356  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4357  // If they are the same, no error.
4358  if (CalcEffectiveSubGroup(S.getASTContext(), S.getLangOpts(), SYCLKernel) ==
4359  CalcEffectiveSubGroup(S.getASTContext(), S.getLangOpts(), FD))
4360  return;
4361 
4362  // No need to validate __spirv routines here since they
4363  // are mapped to the equivalent SPIRV operations.
4364  const IdentifierInfo *II = FD->getIdentifier();
4365  if (II && II->getName().starts_with("__spirv_"))
4366  return;
4367 
4368  // Else we need to figure out why they don't match.
4369  SourceLocation FDAttrLoc = GetSubGroupLoc(FD);
4370  SourceLocation KernelAttrLoc = GetSubGroupLoc(SYCLKernel);
4371 
4372  if (FDAttrLoc.isValid()) {
4373  // This side was caused by an attribute.
4374  S.Diag(FDAttrLoc, diag::err_sycl_mismatch_group_size)
4375  << /*kernel called*/ 0;
4376 
4377  if (KernelAttrLoc.isValid()) {
4378  S.Diag(KernelAttrLoc, diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4379  } else {
4380  // Kernel is 'default'.
4381  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(), diag::note_sycl_kernel_declared_here);
4382  }
4383  return;
4384  }
4385 
4386  // Else this doesn't have an attribute, which can only be caused by this being
4387  // an undefined SYCL_EXTERNAL, and the kernel has an attribute that conflicts.
4388  if (const auto *A = SYCLKernel->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4389  // Don't diagnose this if the kernel got its size from the 'old' attribute
4390  // spelling.
4391  if (!A->isSYCL2020Spelling())
4392  return;
4393  }
4394 
4395  assert(KernelAttrLoc.isValid() && "Kernel doesn't have attribute either?");
4396  S.Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_sycl_mismatch_group_size)
4397  << /*undefined SYCL_EXTERNAL*/ 1;
4398  S.Diag(KernelAttrLoc, diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4399 }
4400 
4401 // Check SYCL2020 Attributes. 2020 attributes don't propogate, they are only
4402 // valid if they match the attribute on the kernel. Note that this is a slight
4403 // difference from what the spec says, which says these attributes are only
4404 // valid on SYCL Kernels and SYCL_EXTERNAL, but we felt that for
4405 // self-documentation purposes that it would be nice to be able to repeat these
4406 // on subsequent functions.
4407 static void CheckSYCL2020Attributes(
4408  SemaSYCL &S, FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel, FunctionDecl *KernelBody,
4409  const llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<FunctionDecl *> &CalledFuncs) {
4410 
4411  if (KernelBody) {
4412  // Make sure the kernel itself has all the 2020 attributes, since we don't
4413  // do propagation of these.
4414  if (auto *A = KernelBody->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>())
4415  if (A->isSYCL2020Spelling())
4416  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4417  if (auto *A = KernelBody->getAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
4418  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4419 
4420  // If the kernel has a body, we should get the attributes for the kernel
4421  // from there instead, so that we get the functor object.
4422  SYCLKernel = KernelBody;
4423  }
4424 
4425  for (auto *FD : CalledFuncs) {
4426  if (FD == SYCLKernel || FD == KernelBody)
4427  continue;
4428  for (auto *Attr : FD->attrs()) {
4429  switch (Attr->getKind()) {
4430  case attr::Kind::IntelReqdSubGroupSize:
4431  // Pre SYCL2020 spellings handled during collection.
4432  if (!cast<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(Attr)->isSYCL2020Spelling())
4433  break;
4434  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4435  case attr::Kind::IntelNamedSubGroupSize:
4436  CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(S, SYCLKernel, FD);
4437  break;
4438  case attr::Kind::SYCLDevice:
4439  // If a SYCL_EXTERNAL function is not defined in this TU, its necessary
4440  // that it has a compatible sub-group-size. Don't diagnose if it has a
4441  // sub-group attribute, we can count on the other checks to catch this.
4442  if (!FD->isDefined() && !FD->hasAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>() &&
4443  !FD->hasAttr<IntelNamedSubGroupSizeAttr>())
4444  CheckSYCL2020SubGroupSizes(S, SYCLKernel, FD);
4445  break;
4446  default:
4447  break;
4448  }
4449  }
4450  }
4451 }
4452 
4453 static void PropagateAndDiagnoseDeviceAttr(
4454  SemaSYCL &S, const SingleDeviceFunctionTracker &Tracker, Attr *A,
4455  FunctionDecl *SYCLKernel, FunctionDecl *KernelBody) {
4456  switch (A->getKind()) {
4457  case attr::Kind::IntelReqdSubGroupSize: {
4458  auto *Attr = cast<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(A);
4459 
4460  if (Attr->isSYCL2020Spelling())
4461  break;
4462  const auto *KBSimdAttr =
4463  KernelBody ? KernelBody->getAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>() : nullptr;
4464  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4465  if (getIntExprValue(Existing->getValue(), S.getASTContext()) !=
4466  getIntExprValue(Attr->getValue(), S.getASTContext())) {
4467  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
4468  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
4469  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4470  S.Diag(Attr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4471  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
4472  }
4473  } else if (KBSimdAttr &&
4474  (getIntExprValue(Attr->getValue(), S.getASTContext()) != 1)) {
4475  reportConflictingAttrs(S, KernelBody, KBSimdAttr, Attr);
4476  } else {
4477  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4478  }
4479  break;
4480  }
4481  case attr::Kind::SYCLReqdWorkGroupSize: {
4482  auto *RWGSA = cast<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(A);
4483  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4484  if (S.SemaRef.AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(
4485  Existing->getXDim(), Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim(),
4486  RWGSA->getXDim(), RWGSA->getYDim(), RWGSA->getZDim())) {
4487  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
4488  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
4489  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4490  S.Diag(RWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4491  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
4492  }
4493  } else if (auto *Existing =
4494  SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4495  if (S.SemaRef.CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(
4496  RWGSA->getXDim(), RWGSA->getYDim(), RWGSA->getZDim(),
4497  Existing->getXDim(), Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim())) {
4498  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
4499  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
4500  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4501  S.Diag(RWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4502  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
4503  } else {
4504  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4505  }
4506  } else {
4507  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4508  }
4509  break;
4510  }
4511  case attr::Kind::SYCLWorkGroupSizeHint: {
4512  auto *WGSH = cast<SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr>(A);
4513  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr>()) {
4514  if (S.SemaRef.AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(
4515  Existing->getXDim(), Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim(),
4516  WGSH->getXDim(), WGSH->getYDim(), WGSH->getZDim())) {
4517  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
4518  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
4519  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4520  S.Diag(WGSH->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4521  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
4522  }
4523  }
4524  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4525  break;
4526  }
4527  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSize: {
4528  auto *SIMWGSA = cast<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>(A);
4529  if (auto *Existing = SYCLKernel->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4530  if (S.SemaRef.CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(
4531  Existing->getXDim(), Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim(),
4532  SIMWGSA->getXDim(), SIMWGSA->getYDim(), SIMWGSA->getZDim())) {
4533  S.Diag(SYCLKernel->getLocation(),
4534  diag::err_conflicting_sycl_kernel_attributes);
4535  S.Diag(Existing->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4536  S.Diag(SIMWGSA->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4537  SYCLKernel->setInvalidDecl();
4538  } else {
4539  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4540  }
4541  } else {
4542  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4543  }
4544  break;
4545  }
4546  case attr::Kind::SYCLSimd:
4547  if (KernelBody && !KernelBody->getAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>()) {
4548  // Usual kernel can't call ESIMD functions.
4549  S.Diag(KernelBody->getLocation(),
4550  diag::err_sycl_function_attribute_mismatch)
4551  << A;
4552  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_attribute);
4553  KernelBody->setInvalidDecl();
4554  break;
4555  }
4556  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4557  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelKernelArgsRestrict:
4558  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItems:
4559  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhz:
4560  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDim:
4561  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMinWorkGroupsPerComputeUnit:
4562  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupsPerMultiprocessor:
4563  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffset:
4564  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelLoopFuse:
4565  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelMaxConcurrency:
4566  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelDisableLoopPipelining:
4567  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelInitiationInterval:
4568  case attr::Kind::SYCLIntelUseStallEnableClusters:
4569  case attr::Kind::SYCLDeviceHas:
4570  case attr::Kind::SYCLAddIRAttributesFunction:
4571  SYCLKernel->addAttr(A);
4572  break;
4573  case attr::Kind::IntelNamedSubGroupSize:
4574  // Nothing to do here, handled in the SYCL2020 spelling.
4575  break;
4576  // TODO: vec_len_hint should be handled here
4577  default:
4578  // Seeing this means that CollectPossibleKernelAttributes was
4579  // updated while this switch wasn't...or something went wrong
4580  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected attribute was collected by "
4581  "CollectPossibleKernelAttributes");
4582  }
4583 }
4584 
4585 void SemaSYCL::MarkDevices() {
4586  // This Tracker object ensures that the SyclDeviceDecls collection includes
4587  // the SYCL_EXTERNAL functions, and manages the diagnostics for all of the
4588  // functions in the kernel.
4589  DeviceFunctionTracker Tracker(*this);
4590 
4591  for (Decl *D : syclDeviceDecls()) {
4592  auto *SYCLKernel = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
4593 
4594  // This type does the actual analysis on a per-kernel basis. It does this to
4595  // make sure that we're only ever dealing with the context of a single
4596  // kernel at a time.
4597  SingleDeviceFunctionTracker T{Tracker, SYCLKernel};
4598 
4599  CheckSYCL2020Attributes(*this, T.GetSYCLKernel(), T.GetKernelBody(),
4600  T.GetDeviceFunctions());
4601  for (auto *A : T.GetCollectedAttributes())
4602  PropagateAndDiagnoseDeviceAttr(*this, T, A, T.GetSYCLKernel(),
4603  T.GetKernelBody());
4604  SemaRef.CheckSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttrConflicts(T.GetSYCLKernel());
4605  }
4606 }

4608 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4610 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4611 
4612 Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder
4613 SemaSYCL::DiagIfDeviceCode(SourceLocation Loc, unsigned DiagID,
4614  DeviceDiagnosticReason Reason) {
4615  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4616  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4617  FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(SemaRef.getCurLexicalContext());
4618  SemaDiagnosticBuilder::Kind DiagKind = [this, FD, Reason] {
4619  if (DiagnosingSYCLKernel)
4620  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_ImmediateWithCallStack;
4621  if (!FD)
4622  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Nop;
4623  if (SemaRef.getEmissionStatus(FD) ==
4624  Sema::FunctionEmissionStatus::Emitted) {
4625  // Skip the diagnostic if we know it won't be emitted.
4626  if ((SemaRef.getEmissionReason(FD) & Reason) ==
4627  Sema::DeviceDiagnosticReason::None)
4628  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Nop;
4629 
4630  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_ImmediateWithCallStack;
4631  }
4632  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder::K_Deferred;
4633  }();
4634  return SemaDiagnosticBuilder(DiagKind, Loc, DiagID, FD, SemaRef, Reason);
4635 }
4636 
4637 void SemaSYCL::deepTypeCheckForDevice(SourceLocation UsedAt,
4638  llvm::DenseSet<QualType> Visited,
4639  ValueDecl *DeclToCheck) {
4640  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4641  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4642  // Emit notes only for the first discovered declaration of unsupported type
4643  // to avoid mess of notes. This flag is to track that error already happened.
4644  bool NeedToEmitNotes = true;
4645 
4646  auto Check = [&](QualType TypeToCheck, const ValueDecl *D) {
4647  bool ErrorFound = false;
4648  if (isZeroSizedArray(*this, TypeToCheck)) {
4649  DiagIfDeviceCode(UsedAt, diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size) << 1;
4650  ErrorFound = true;
4651  }
4652  // Checks for other types can also be done here.
4653  if (ErrorFound) {
4654  if (NeedToEmitNotes) {
4655  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D))
4656  DiagIfDeviceCode(FD->getLocation(),
4657  diag::note_illegal_field_declared_here)
4658  << FD->getType()->isPointerType() << FD->getType();
4659  else
4660  DiagIfDeviceCode(D->getLocation(), diag::note_declared_at);
4661  }
4662  }
4663 
4664  return ErrorFound;
4665  };
4666 
4667  // In case we have a Record used do the DFS for a bad field.
4668  SmallVector<const ValueDecl *, 4> StackForRecursion;
4669  StackForRecursion.push_back(DeclToCheck);
4670 
4671  // While doing DFS save how we get there to emit a nice set of notes.
4672  SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 4> History;
4673  History.push_back(nullptr);
4674 
4675  do {
4676  const ValueDecl *Next = StackForRecursion.pop_back_val();
4677  if (!Next) {
4678  assert(!History.empty());
4679  // Found a marker, we have gone up a level.
4680  History.pop_back();
4681  continue;
4682  }
4683  QualType NextTy = Next->getType();
4684 
4685  if (!Visited.insert(NextTy).second)
4686  continue;
4687 
4688  auto EmitHistory = [&]() {
4689  // The first element is always nullptr.
4690  for (uint64_t Index = 1; Index < History.size(); ++Index) {
4691  DiagIfDeviceCode(History[Index]->getLocation(),
4692  diag::note_within_field_of_type)
4693  << History[Index]->getType();
4694  }
4695  };
4696 
4697  if (Check(NextTy, Next)) {
4698  if (NeedToEmitNotes)
4699  EmitHistory();
4700  NeedToEmitNotes = false;
4701  }
4702 
4703  // In case pointer/array/reference type is met get pointee type, then
4704  // proceed with that type.
4705  while (NextTy->isAnyPointerType() || NextTy->isArrayType() ||
4706  NextTy->isReferenceType()) {
4707  if (NextTy->isArrayType())
4708  NextTy = QualType{NextTy->getArrayElementTypeNoTypeQual(), 0};
4709  else
4710  NextTy = NextTy->getPointeeType();
4711  if (Check(NextTy, Next)) {
4712  if (NeedToEmitNotes)
4713  EmitHistory();
4714  NeedToEmitNotes = false;
4715  }
4716  }
4717 
4718  if (const auto *RecDecl = NextTy->getAsRecordDecl()) {
4719  if (auto *NextFD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(Next))
4720  History.push_back(NextFD);
4721  // When nullptr is discovered, this means we've gone back up a level, so
4722  // the history should be cleaned.
4723  StackForRecursion.push_back(nullptr);
4724  llvm::copy(RecDecl->fields(), std::back_inserter(StackForRecursion));
4725  }
4726  } while (!StackForRecursion.empty());
4727 }
4728 
4729 void SemaSYCL::finalizeSYCLDelayedAnalysis(const FunctionDecl *Caller,
4730  const FunctionDecl *Callee,
4731  SourceLocation Loc,
4732  DeviceDiagnosticReason Reason) {
4733  Callee = Callee->getMostRecentDecl();
4734 
4735  // If the reason for the emission of this diagnostic is not SYCL-specific,
4736  // and it is not known to be reachable from a routine on device, do not
4737  // issue a diagnostic.
4738  if ((Reason & DeviceDiagnosticReason::Sycl) == DeviceDiagnosticReason::None &&
4739  !isFDReachableFromSyclDevice(Callee, Caller))
4740  return;
4741 
4742  // If Callee has a SYCL attribute, no diagnostic needed.
4743  if (Callee->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>() || Callee->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>())
4744  return;
4745 
4746  // If Callee has a CUDA device attribute, no diagnostic needed.
4747  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && Callee->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
4748  return;
4749 
4750  // Diagnose if this is an undefined function and it is not a builtin.
4751  // Currently, there is an exception of "__failed_assertion" in libstdc++-11,
4752  // this undefined function is used to trigger a compiling error.
4753  if (!Callee->isDefined() && !Callee->getBuiltinID() &&
4754  !Callee->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction() &&
4755  !isSYCLUndefinedAllowed(Callee, SemaRef.getSourceManager())) {
4756  Diag(Loc, diag::err_sycl_restrict) << SemaSYCL::KernelCallUndefinedFunction;
4757  Diag(Callee->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl) << Callee;
4758  Diag(Caller->getLocation(), diag::note_called_by) << Caller;
4759  }
4760 }
4761 
4762 bool SemaSYCL::checkAllowedSYCLInitializer(VarDecl *VD) {
4763  assert(getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
4764  "Should only be called during SYCL compilation");
4765 
4766  if (VD->isInvalidDecl() || !VD->hasInit() || !VD->hasGlobalStorage())
4767  return true;
4768 
4769  const Expr *Init = VD->getInit();
4770  bool ValueDependent = Init && Init->isValueDependent();
4771  bool isConstantInit = Init && !ValueDependent &&
4772  Init->isConstantInitializer(getASTContext(), false);
4773  if (!VD->isConstexpr() && Init && !ValueDependent && !isConstantInit)
4774  return false;
4775 
4776  return true;
4777 }

4783 /// Returns a string ID of given parameter kind - used in header
4784 /// emission.
4785 static const char *paramKind2Str(KernelParamKind K) {
4786 #define CASE(x) \
4787  case SYCLIntegrationHeader::kind_##x: \
4788  return "kind_" #x
4789  switch (K) {
4790  CASE(accessor);
4791  CASE(std_layout);
4792  CASE(sampler);
4793  CASE(stream);
4794  CASE(specialization_constants_buffer);
4795  CASE(pointer);
4796  }
4797  return "<ERROR>";
4798 
4799 #undef CASE
4800 }
4801 
4802 // Emits forward declarations of classes and template classes on which
4803 // declaration of given type depends.
4804 // For example, consider SimpleVadd
4805 // class specialization in parallel_for below:
4806 //
4807 // template <typename T1, unsigned int N, typename ... T2>
4808 // class SimpleVadd;
4809 // ...
4810 // template <unsigned int N, typename T1, typename ... T2>
4811 // void simple_vadd(const std::array<T1, N>& VA, const std::array<T1, N>&
4812 // VB,
4813 // std::array<T1, N>& VC, int param, T2 ... varargs) {
4814 // ...
4815 // deviceQueue.submit([&](sycl::handler& cgh) {
4816 // ...
4817 // cgh.parallel_for<class SimpleVadd<T1, N, T2...>>(...)
4818 // ...
4819 // }
4820 // ...
4821 // }
4822 // ...
4823 // class MyClass {...};
4824 // template <typename T> class MyInnerTmplClass { ... }
4825 // template <typename T> class MyTmplClass { ... }
4826 // ...
4827 // MyClass *c = new MyClass();
4828 // MyInnerTmplClass<MyClass**> c1(&c);
4829 // simple_vadd(A, B, C, 5, 'a', 1.f,
4830 // new MyTmplClass<MyInnerTmplClass<MyClass**>>(c1));
4831 //
4832 // it will generate the following forward declarations:
4833 // class MyClass;
4834 // template <typename T> class MyInnerTmplClass;
4835 // template <typename T> class MyTmplClass;
4836 // template <typename T1, unsigned int N, typename ...T2> class SimpleVadd;
4837 //
4838 class SYCLFwdDeclEmitter
4839  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>,
4840  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter> {
4841  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>;
4842  using InnerTemplArgVisitor = ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLFwdDeclEmitter>;
4843  raw_ostream &OS;
4844  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const NamedDecl *, 4> Printed;
4845  PrintingPolicy Policy;
4846 
4847  void printForwardDecl(NamedDecl *D) {
4848  // wrap the declaration into namespaces if needed
4849  unsigned NamespaceCnt = 0;
4850  std::string NSStr = "";
4851  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext();
4852 
4853  while (DC) {
4854  if (const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC)) {
4855  ++NamespaceCnt;
4856  StringRef NSInlinePrefix = NS->isInline() ? "inline " : "";
4857  NSStr.insert(
4858  0,
4859  Twine(NSInlinePrefix + "namespace " + NS->getName() + " { ").str());
4860  DC = NS->getDeclContext();
4861  } else {
4862  // We should be able to handle a subset of the decl-context types to
4863  // make our namespaces for forward declarations as specific as possible,
4864  // so just skip them here. We can't use their names, since they would
4865  // not be forward declarable, but we can try to make them as specific as
4866  // possible.
4867  // This permits things such as:
4868  // namespace N1 { void foo() { kernel<class K>(...); }}
4869  // and
4870  // namespace N2 { void foo() { kernel<class K>(...); }}
4871  // to co-exist, despite technically being against the SYCL rules.
4872  // See SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter for the corresponding part that prints
4873  // the kernel information for this type. These two must match.
4874  if (isa<FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
4875  DC = cast<Decl>(DC)->getDeclContext();
4876  } else {
4877  break;
4878  }
4879  }
4880  }
4881  OS << NSStr;
4882  if (NamespaceCnt > 0)
4883  OS << "\n";
4884 
4885  D->print(OS, Policy);
4886 
4887  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
4888  QualType T = ED->getIntegerType().getCanonicalType();
4889  // Backup since getIntegerType() returns null for enum forward
4890  // declaration with no fixed underlying type
4891  if (T.isNull())
4892  T = ED->getPromotionType();
4893  OS << " : " << T.getAsString();
4894  }
4895 
4896  OS << ";\n";
4897 
4898  // print closing braces for namespaces if needed
4899  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NamespaceCnt; ++I)
4900  OS << "}";
4901  if (NamespaceCnt > 0)
4902  OS << "\n";
4903  }
4904 
4905  // Checks if we've already printed forward declaration and prints it if not.
4906  void checkAndEmitForwardDecl(NamedDecl *D) {
4907  if (Printed.insert(D).second)
4908  printForwardDecl(D);
4909  }
4910 
4911  void VisitTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
4912  for (size_t I = 0, E = Args.size(); I < E; ++I)
4913  Visit(Args[I]);
4914  }
4915 
4916 public:
4917  SYCLFwdDeclEmitter(raw_ostream &OS, const LangOptions &LO)
4918  : OS(OS), Policy(LO) {
4919  Policy.adjustForCPlusPlusFwdDecl();
4920  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
4921  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
4922  Policy.PrintCanonicalTypes = true;
4923  Policy.SkipCanonicalizationOfTemplateTypeParms = true;
4924  Policy.SuppressFinalSpecifier = true;
4925  }
4926 
4927  void Visit(QualType T) {
4928  if (T.isNull())
4929  return;
4930  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(T.getTypePtr());
4931  }
4932 
4933  void VisitReferenceType(const ReferenceType *RT) {
4934  // Our forward declarations don't care about references, so we should just
4935  // ignore the reference and continue on.
4936  Visit(RT->getPointeeType());
4937  }
4938 
4939  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4940  if (TA.isNull())
4941  return;
4942  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
4943  }
4944 
4945  void VisitPointerType(const PointerType *T) {
4946  // Peel off the pointer types.
4947  QualType PT = T->getPointeeType();
4948  while (PT->isPointerType())
4949  PT = PT->getPointeeType();
4950  Visit(PT);
4951  }
4952 
4953  void VisitTagType(const TagType *T) {
4954  TagDecl *TD = T->getDecl();
4955  if (const auto *TSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(TD)) {
4956  // - first, recurse into template parameters and emit needed forward
4957  // declarations
4958  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
4959  VisitTemplateArgs(Args);
4960  // - second, emit forward declaration for the template class being
4961  // specialized
4962  ClassTemplateDecl *CTD = TSD->getSpecializedTemplate();
4963  assert(CTD && "template declaration must be available");
4964 
4965  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(CTD);
4966  return;
4967  }
4968  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(TD);
4969  }
4970 
4971  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4972  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
4973  Visit(T);
4974  }
4975 
4976  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4977  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
4978  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
4979  VisitTagType(ET);
4980  }
4981 
4982  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
4983  // recursion is not required, since the maximum possible nesting level
4984  // equals two for template argument
4985  //
4986  // for example:
4987  // template <typename T> class Bar;
4988  // template <template <typename> class> class Baz;
4989  // template <template <template <typename> class> class T>
4990  // class Foo;
4991  //
4992  // The Baz is a template class. The Baz<Bar> is a class. The class Foo
4993  // should be specialized with template class, not a class. The correct
4994  // specialization of template class Foo is Foo<Baz>. The incorrect
4995  // specialization of template class Foo is Foo<Baz<Bar>>. In this case
4996  // template class Foo specialized by class Baz<Bar>, not a template
4997  // class template <template <typename> class> class T as it should.
4998  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
4999  assert(TD && "template declaration must be available");
5000  TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams = TD->getTemplateParameters();
5001  for (NamedDecl *P : *TemplateParams) {
5002  // If template template parameter type has an enum value template
5003  // parameter, forward declaration of enum type is required. Only enum
5004  // values (not types) need to be handled. For example, consider the
5005  // following kernel name type:
5006  //
5007  // template <typename EnumTypeOut, template <EnumValueIn EnumValue,
5008  // typename TypeIn> class T> class Foo;
5009  //
5010  // The correct specialization for Foo (with enum type) is:
5011  // Foo<EnumTypeOut, Baz>, where Baz is a template class.
5012  //
5013  // Therefore the forward class declarations generated in the
5014  // integration header are:
5015  // template <EnumValueIn EnumValue, typename TypeIn> class Baz;
5016  // template <typename EnumTypeOut, template <EnumValueIn EnumValue,
5017  // typename EnumTypeIn> class T> class Foo;
5018  //
5019  // This requires the following enum forward declarations:
5020  // enum class EnumTypeOut : int; (Used to template Foo)
5021  // enum class EnumValueIn : int; (Used to template Baz)
5022  if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *TemplateParam =
5023  dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(P))
5024  if (const EnumType *ET = TemplateParam->getType()->getAs<EnumType>())
5025  VisitTagType(ET);
5026  }
5027  checkAndEmitForwardDecl(TD);
5028  }
5029 
5030  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5031  VisitTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
5032  }
5033 };
5034 
5035 class SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter
5036  : public TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>,
5037  public ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter> {
5038  using InnerTypeVisitor = TypeVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>;
5039  using InnerTemplArgVisitor =
5040  ConstTemplateArgumentVisitor<SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter>;
5041  raw_ostream &OS;
5042  PrintingPolicy &Policy;
5043 
5044  void printTemplateArgs(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
5045  for (size_t I = 0, E = Args.size(); I < E; ++I) {
5046  const TemplateArgument &Arg = Args[I];
5047  // If argument is an empty pack argument, skip printing comma and
5048  // argument.
5049  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::ArgKind::Pack && !Arg.pack_size())
5050  continue;
5051 
5052  if (I)
5053  OS << ", ";
5054 
5055  Visit(Arg);
5056  }
5057  }
5058 
5059  void VisitQualifiers(Qualifiers Quals) {
5060  Quals.print(OS, Policy, /*appendSpaceIfNotEmpty*/ true);
5061  }
5062 
5063  // Use recursion to print the namespace-qualified name for the purposes of the
5064  // canonical sycl example of a type being created in the kernel call.
5065  void PrintNamespaceScopes(const DeclContext *DC) {
5066  if (isa<NamespaceDecl, FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
5067  PrintNamespaceScopes(DC->getParent());
5068 
5069  const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC);
5070  if (NS && !NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
5071  OS << NS->getName() << "::";
5072  }
5073  }
5074 
5075 public:
5076  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter(raw_ostream &OS, PrintingPolicy &Policy)
5077  : OS(OS), Policy(Policy) {}
5078 
5079  void Visit(QualType T) {
5080  if (T.isNull())
5081  return;
5082 
5083  QualType CT = T.getCanonicalType();
5084  VisitQualifiers(CT.getQualifiers());
5085 
5086  InnerTypeVisitor::Visit(CT.getTypePtr());
5087  }
5088 
5089  void VisitType(const Type *T) {
5090  OS << QualType::getAsString(T, Qualifiers(), Policy);
5091  }
5092 
5093  void Visit(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5094  if (TA.isNull())
5095  return;
5096  InnerTemplArgVisitor::Visit(TA);
5097  }
5098 
5099  void VisitTagType(const TagType *T) {
5100  TagDecl *RD = T->getDecl();
5101  if (const auto *TSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
5102 
5103  // Print template class name
5104  TSD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy, /*WithGlobalNsPrefix*/ true);
5105 
5106  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args = TSD->getTemplateArgs().asArray();
5107  OS << "<";
5108  printTemplateArgs(Args);
5109  OS << ">";
5110 
5111  return;
5112  }
5113 
5114  // Handle the canonical sycl example where the type is created for the first
5115  // time in the kernel naming. We want to qualify this as fully as we can,
5116  // but not in a way that won't be forward declarable. See
5117  // SYCLFwdDeclEmitter::printForwardDecl for the corresponding list for
5118  // printing the forward declaration, these two must match.
5119  DeclContext *DC = RD->getDeclContext();
5120  if (isa<FunctionDecl, RecordDecl, LinkageSpecDecl>(DC)) {
5121  PrintNamespaceScopes(DC);
5122  RD->printName(OS, Policy);
5123  return;
5124  }
5125 
5126  const NamespaceDecl *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(RD->getDeclContext());
5127  RD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy, !(NS && NS->isAnonymousNamespace()));
5128  }
5129 
5130  void VisitTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5131  TA.print(Policy, OS, false /* IncludeType */);
5132  }
5133 
5134  void VisitTypeTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5135  Policy.SuppressTagKeyword = true;
5136  QualType T = TA.getAsType();
5137  Visit(T);
5138  Policy.SuppressTagKeyword = false;
5139  }
5140 
5141  void VisitIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5142  QualType T = TA.getIntegralType();
5143  if (const EnumType *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>()) {
5144  const llvm::APSInt &Val = TA.getAsIntegral();
5145  OS << "static_cast<";
5146  ET->getDecl()->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy,
5147  /*WithGlobalNsPrefix*/ true);
5148  OS << ">(" << Val << ")";
5149  } else {
5150  TA.print(Policy, OS, false /* IncludeType */);
5151  }
5152  }
5153 
5154  void VisitTemplateTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5155  TemplateDecl *TD = TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
5156  TD->printQualifiedName(OS, Policy);
5157  }
5158 
5159  void VisitPackTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &TA) {
5160  printTemplateArgs(TA.getPackAsArray());
5161  }
5162 };
5163 
5164 static void OutputStableNameChar(raw_ostream &O, char C) {
5165  // If it is reliably printable, print in the integration header as a
5166  // character. Else just print it as the integral representation.
5167  if (llvm::isPrint(C))
5168  O << '\'' << C << '\'';
5169  else
5170  O << static_cast<short>(C);
5171 }
5172 
5173 static void OutputStableNameInChars(raw_ostream &O, StringRef Name) {
5174  assert(!Name.empty() && "Expected a nonempty string!");
5175  OutputStableNameChar(O, Name[0]);
5176 
5177  for (char C : Name.substr(1)) {
5178  O << ", ";
5179  OutputStableNameChar(O, C);
5180  }
5181 }
5182 
5183 void SYCLIntegrationHeader::emit(raw_ostream &O) {
5184  O << "// This is auto-generated SYCL integration header.\n";
5185  O << "\n";
5186 
5187  O << "#include <sycl/detail/defines_elementary.hpp>\n";
5188  O << "#include <sycl/detail/kernel_desc.hpp>\n";
5189 
5190  O << "\n";
5191 
5192  LangOptions LO;
5193  PrintingPolicy Policy(LO);
5194  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
5195  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
5196  // Disable printing anonymous tag locations because on Windows
5197  // file path separators are treated as escape sequences and cause errors
5198  // when integration header is compiled with host compiler.
5199  Policy.AnonymousTagLocations = 0;
5200  SYCLFwdDeclEmitter FwdDeclEmitter(O, S.getLangOpts());
5201 
5202  // Predefines which need to be set for custom host compilation
5203  // must be defined in integration header.
5204  for (const std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> &Macro :
5205  getSYCLVersionMacros(S.getLangOpts())) {
5206  O << "#ifndef " << Macro.first << '\n';
5207  O << "#define " << Macro.first << " " << Macro.second << '\n';
5208  O << "#endif //" << Macro.first << "\n\n";
5209  }
5210 
5211  switch (S.getLangOpts().getSYCLRangeRounding()) {
5212  case LangOptions::SYCLRangeRoundingPreference::Disable:
5213  O << "#ifndef __SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ \n";
5214  O << "#define __SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ 1\n";
5215  O << "#endif //__SYCL_DISABLE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__\n\n";
5216  break;
5217  case LangOptions::SYCLRangeRoundingPreference::Force:
5218  O << "#ifndef __SYCL_FORCE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ \n";
5219  O << "#define __SYCL_FORCE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ 1\n";
5220  O << "#endif //__SYCL_FORCE_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__\n\n";
5221  break;
5222  default:
5223  break;
5224  }
5225 
5226  if (S.getLangOpts().SYCLExperimentalRangeRounding) {
5227  O << "#ifndef __SYCL_EXP_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ \n";
5228  O << "#define __SYCL_EXP_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__ 1\n";
5229  O << "#endif //__SYCL_EXP_PARALLEL_FOR_RANGE_ROUNDING__\n\n";
5230  }
5231 
5232  if (SpecConsts.size() > 0) {
5233  O << "// Forward declarations of templated spec constant types:\n";
5234  for (const auto &SC : SpecConsts)
5235  FwdDeclEmitter.Visit(SC.first);
5236  O << "\n";
5237 
5238  // Remove duplicates.
5239  std::sort(SpecConsts.begin(), SpecConsts.end(),
5240  [](const SpecConstID &SC1, const SpecConstID &SC2) {
5241  // Sort by string IDs for stable spec consts order in the
5242  // header.
5243  return SC1.second.compare(SC2.second) < 0;
5244  });
5245  SpecConstID *End =
5246  std::unique(SpecConsts.begin(), SpecConsts.end(),
5247  [](const SpecConstID &SC1, const SpecConstID &SC2) {
5248  // Here can do faster comparison of types.
5249  return SC1.first == SC2.first;
5250  });
5251 
5252  O << "// Specialization constants IDs:\n";
5253  for (const auto &P : llvm::make_range(SpecConsts.begin(), End)) {
5254  O << "template <> struct sycl::detail::SpecConstantInfo<";
5255  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
5256  Printer.Visit(P.first);
5257  O << "> {\n";
5258  O << " static constexpr const char* getName() {\n";
5259  O << " return \"" << P.second << "\";\n";
5260  O << " }\n";
5261  O << "};\n";
5262  }
5263  }
5264 
5265  O << "// Forward declarations of templated kernel function types:\n";
5266  for (const KernelDesc &K : KernelDescs)
5267  if (!K.IsUnnamedKernel)
5268  FwdDeclEmitter.Visit(K.NameType);
5269  O << "\n";
5270 
5271  O << "namespace sycl {\n";
5272  O << "inline namespace _V1 {\n";
5273  O << "namespace detail {\n";
5274 
5275  // Generate declaration of variable of type __sycl_device_global_registration
5276  // whose sole purpose is to run its constructor before the application's
5277  // main() function.
5278 
5279  if (NeedToEmitDeviceGlobalRegistration) {
5280  O << "namespace {\n";
5281 
5282  O << "class __sycl_device_global_registration {\n";
5283  O << "public:\n";
5284  O << " __sycl_device_global_registration() noexcept;\n";
5285  O << "};\n";
5286  O << "__sycl_device_global_registration __sycl_device_global_registrar;\n";
5287 
5288  O << "} // namespace\n";
5289 
5290  O << "\n";
5291  }
5292 
5293  // Generate declaration of variable of type __sycl_host_pipe_registration
5294  // whose sole purpose is to run its constructor before the application's
5295  // main() function.
5296  if (NeedToEmitHostPipeRegistration) {
5297  O << "namespace {\n";
5298 
5299  O << "class __sycl_host_pipe_registration {\n";
5300  O << "public:\n";
5301  O << " __sycl_host_pipe_registration() noexcept;\n";
5302  O << "};\n";
5303  O << "__sycl_host_pipe_registration __sycl_host_pipe_registrar;\n";
5304 
5305  O << "} // namespace\n";
5306 
5307  O << "\n";
5308  }
5309 
5310 
5311  O << "// names of all kernels defined in the corresponding source\n";
5312  O << "static constexpr\n";
5313  O << "const char* const kernel_names[] = {\n";
5314 
5315  for (unsigned I = 0; I < KernelDescs.size(); I++) {
5316  O << " \"" << KernelDescs[I].Name << "\"";
5317 
5318  if (I < KernelDescs.size() - 1)
5319  O << ",";
5320  O << "\n";
5321  }
5322  O << "};\n\n";
5323 
5324  O << "// array representing signatures of all kernels defined in the\n";
5325  O << "// corresponding source\n";
5326  O << "static constexpr\n";
5327  O << "const kernel_param_desc_t kernel_signatures[] = {\n";
5328 
5329  for (unsigned I = 0; I < KernelDescs.size(); I++) {
5330  auto &K = KernelDescs[I];
5331  O << " //--- " << K.Name << "\n";
5332 
5333  for (const auto &P : K.Params) {
5334  std::string TyStr = paramKind2Str(P.Kind);
5335  O << " { kernel_param_kind_t::" << TyStr << ", ";
5336  O << P.Info << ", " << P.Offset << " },\n";
5337  }
5338  O << "\n";
5339  }
5340 
5341  // Sentinel in place for 2 reasons:
5342  // 1- to make sure we don't get a warning because this collection is empty.
5343  // 2- to provide an obvious value that we can use when debugging to see that
5344  // we have left valid kernel information.
5345  // integer-field values are negative, so they are obviously invalid, notable
5346  // enough to 'stick out' and 'negative enough' to not be easily reachable by a
5347  // mathematical error.
5348  O << " { kernel_param_kind_t::kind_invalid, -987654321, -987654321 }, \n";
5349  O << "};\n\n";
5350 
5351  O << "// Specializations of KernelInfo for kernel function types:\n";
5352  unsigned CurStart = 0;
5353 
5354  for (const KernelDesc &K : KernelDescs) {
5355  const size_t N = K.Params.size();
5356  PresumedLoc PLoc = S.getASTContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(
5357  S.getASTContext()
5358  .getSourceManager()
5359  .getExpansionRange(K.KernelLocation)
5360  .getEnd());
5361  if (K.IsUnnamedKernel) {
5362  O << "template <> struct KernelInfoData<";
5363  OutputStableNameInChars(O, K.StableName);
5364  O << "> {\n";
5365  } else {
5366  O << "template <> struct KernelInfo<";
5367  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
5368  Printer.Visit(K.NameType);
5369  O << "> {\n";
5370  }
5371 
5372  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5373  O << " static constexpr const char* getName() { return \"" << K.Name
5374  << "\"; }\n";
5375  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5376  O << " static constexpr unsigned getNumParams() { return " << N << "; }\n";
5377  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5378  O << " static constexpr const kernel_param_desc_t& ";
5379  O << "getParamDesc(unsigned i) {\n";
5380  O << " return kernel_signatures[i+" << CurStart << "];\n";
5381  O << " }\n";
5382  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5383  O << " static constexpr bool isESIMD() { return " << K.IsESIMDKernel
5384  << "; }\n";
5385  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5386  O << " static constexpr const char* getFileName() {\n";
5387  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
5388  O << " return \""
5389  << std::string(PLoc.getFilename())
5390  .substr(std::string(PLoc.getFilename()).find_last_of("/\\") + 1);
5391  O << "\";\n";
5392  O << "#else\n";
5393  O << " return \"\";\n";
5394  O << "#endif\n";
5395  O << " }\n";
5396  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5397  O << " static constexpr const char* getFunctionName() {\n";
5398  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
5399  O << " return \"";
5400  SYCLKernelNameTypePrinter Printer(O, Policy);
5401  Printer.Visit(K.NameType);
5402  O << "\";\n";
5403  O << "#else\n";
5404  O << " return \"\";\n";
5405  O << "#endif\n";
5406  O << " }\n";
5407  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5408  O << " static constexpr unsigned getLineNumber() {\n";
5409  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
5410  O << " return " << PLoc.getLine() << ";\n";
5411  O << "#else\n";
5412  O << " return 0;\n";
5413  O << "#endif\n";
5414  O << " }\n";
5415  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5416  O << " static constexpr unsigned getColumnNumber() {\n";
5417  O << "#ifndef NDEBUG\n";
5418  O << " return " << PLoc.getColumn() << ";\n";
5419  O << "#else\n";
5420  O << " return 0;\n";
5421  O << "#endif\n";
5422  O << " }\n";
5423  StringRef ReturnType = (S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getInt64Type() ==
5424  TargetInfo::SignedLong)
5425  ? "long"
5426  : "long long";
5427  O << " // Returns the size of the kernel object in bytes.\n";
5428  O << " __SYCL_DLL_LOCAL\n";
5429  O << " static constexpr " << ReturnType << " getKernelSize() { return "
5430  << K.ObjSize << "; }\n";
5431  O << "};\n";
5432  CurStart += N;
5433  }
5434  O << "\n";
5435  O << "} // namespace detail\n";
5436  O << "} // namespace _V1\n";
5437  O << "} // namespace sycl\n";
5438  O << "\n";
5439 }

5441 bool SYCLIntegrationHeader::emit(StringRef IntHeaderName) {
5442  if (IntHeaderName.empty())
5443  return false;
5444  int IntHeaderFD = 0;
5445  std::error_code EC =
5446  llvm::sys::fs::openFileForWrite(IntHeaderName, IntHeaderFD);
5447  if (EC) {
5448  llvm::errs() << "Error: " << EC.message() << "\n";
5449  // compilation will fail on absent include file - don't need to fail here
5450  return false;
5451  }
5452  llvm::raw_fd_ostream Out(IntHeaderFD, true /*close in destructor*/);
5453  emit(Out);
5454  return true;
5455 }

5487 void SYCLIntegrationFooter::addVarDecl(const VarDecl *VD) {
5488  // Variable template declaration can result in an error case of 'nullptr'
5489  // here.
5490  if (!VD)
5491  return;
5492  // Skip the dependent version of these variables, we only care about them
5493  // after instantiation.
5494  if (VD->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext())
5495  return;
5496 
5497  // Skip partial specializations of a variable template, treat other variable
5498  // template instantiations as a VarDecl.
5499  if (isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(VD))
5500  return;
5501  // Step 1: ensure that this is of the correct type template specialization.
5502  if (!SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::specialization_id) &&
5503  !SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::host_pipe) &&
5504  !S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
5505  VD->getType())) {
5506  // Handle the case where this could be a deduced type, such as a deduction
5507  // guide. We have to do this here since this function, unlike most of the
5508  // rest of this file, is called during Sema instead of after it. We will
5509  // also have to filter out after deduction later.
5510  QualType Ty = VD->getType().getCanonicalType();
5511  if (!Ty->isUndeducedType())
5512  return;
5513  }
5514  // Step 2: ensure that this is a static member, or a namespace-scope.
5515  // Note that isLocalVarDeclorParm excludes thread-local and static-local
5516  // intentionally, as there is no way to 'spell' one of those in the
5517  // specialization. We just don't generate the specialization for those, and
5518  // let an error happen during host compilation. To avoid multiple entries for
5519  // redeclarations, variables with external storage are omitted.
5520  if (VD->hasLocalStorage() || VD->isLocalVarDeclOrParm() ||
5521  VD->hasExternalStorage())
5522  return;
5523 
5524  // Step 3: Add to collection.
5525  GlobalVars.push_back(VD);
5526 }
5527 
5528 // Post-compile integration header support.
5529 bool SYCLIntegrationFooter::emit(StringRef IntHeaderName) {
5530  if (IntHeaderName.empty())
5531  return false;
5532  int IntHeaderFD = 0;
5533  std::error_code EC =
5534  llvm::sys::fs::openFileForWrite(IntHeaderName, IntHeaderFD);
5535  if (EC) {
5536  llvm::errs() << "Error: " << EC.message() << "\n";
5537  // compilation will fail on absent include file - don't need to fail here
5538  return false;
5539  }
5540  llvm::raw_fd_ostream Out(IntHeaderFD, true /*close in destructor*/);
5541  return emit(Out);
5542 }
5543 
5544 template <typename BeforeFn, typename AfterFn>
5545 static void PrintNSHelper(BeforeFn Before, AfterFn After, raw_ostream &OS,
5546  const DeclContext *DC) {
5547  if (DC->isTranslationUnit())
5548  return;
5549 
5550  const auto *CurDecl = cast<Decl>(DC);
5551  // Ensure we are in the canonical version, so that we know we have the 'full'
5552  // name of the thing.
5553  CurDecl = CurDecl->getCanonicalDecl();
5554 
5555  // We are intentionally skipping linkage decls and record decls. Namespaces
5556  // can appear in a linkage decl, but not a record decl, so we don't have to
5557  // worry about the names getting messed up from that. We handle record decls
5558  // later when printing the name of the thing.
5559  const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(CurDecl);
5560  if (NS)
5561  Before(OS, NS);
5562 
5563  if (const DeclContext *NewDC = CurDecl->getDeclContext())
5564  PrintNSHelper(Before, After, OS, NewDC);
5565 
5566  if (NS)
5567  After(OS, NS);
5568 }
5569 
5570 static void PrintNamespaces(raw_ostream &OS, const DeclContext *DC) {
5571  PrintNSHelper([](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {},
5572  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {
5573  if (NS->isInline())
5574  OS << "inline ";
5575  OS << "namespace ";
5576  if (!NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
5577  OS << NS->getName() << " ";
5578  OS << "{\n";
5579  },
5580  OS, DC);
5581 }
5582 
5583 static void PrintNSClosingBraces(raw_ostream &OS, const DeclContext *DC) {
5584  PrintNSHelper(
5585  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {
5586  OS << "} // ";
5587  if (NS->isInline())
5588  OS << "inline ";
5589 
5590  OS << "namespace ";
5591  if (!NS->isAnonymousNamespace())
5592  OS << NS->getName();
5593 
5594  OS << '\n';
5595  },
5596  [](raw_ostream &OS, const NamespaceDecl *NS) {}, OS, DC);
5597 }
5598 
5599 static std::string EmitShim(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
5600  const std::string &LastShim,
5601  const NamespaceDecl *AnonNS) {
5602  std::string NewShimName =
5603  "__sycl_detail::__shim_" + std::to_string(ShimCounter) + "()";
5604  // Print opening-namespace
5605  PrintNamespaces(OS, Decl::castToDeclContext(AnonNS));
5606  OS << "namespace __sycl_detail {\n";
5607  OS << "static constexpr decltype(" << LastShim << ") &__shim_" << ShimCounter
5608  << "() {\n";
5609  OS << " return " << LastShim << ";\n";
5610  OS << "}\n";
5611  OS << "} // namespace __sycl_detail\n";
5612  PrintNSClosingBraces(OS, Decl::castToDeclContext(AnonNS));
5613 
5614  ++ShimCounter;
5615  return NewShimName;
5616 }
5617 
5618 // Emit the list of shims required for a DeclContext, calls itself recursively.
5619 static void EmitShims(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
5620  const DeclContext *DC, std::string &NameForLastShim,
5621  PrintingPolicy &Policy) {
5622  if (DC->isTranslationUnit()) {
5623  NameForLastShim = "::" + NameForLastShim;
5624  return;
5625  }
5626 
5627  const auto *CurDecl = cast<Decl>(DC)->getCanonicalDecl();
5628 
5629  // We skip linkage decls, since they don't modify the Qualified name.
5630  if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CurDecl)) {
5631  std::string TemplatedName;
5632  llvm::raw_string_ostream Stream(TemplatedName);
5633  CTSD->getNameForDiagnostic(Stream, Policy, false);
5634  Stream.flush();
5635  NameForLastShim = TemplatedName + "::" + NameForLastShim;
5636  } else if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(CurDecl)) {
5637  NameForLastShim = RD->getNameAsString() + "::" + NameForLastShim;
5638  } else if (const auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(CurDecl)) {
5639  if (ND->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
5640  // Print current shim, reset 'name for last shim'.
5641  NameForLastShim = EmitShim(OS, ShimCounter, NameForLastShim, ND);
5642  } else {
5643  NameForLastShim = ND->getNameAsString() + "::" + NameForLastShim;
5644  }
5645  } else {
5646  // FIXME: I don't believe there are other declarations that these variables
5647  // could possibly find themselves in. LinkageDecls don't change the
5648  // qualified name, so there is nothing to do here. At one point we should
5649  // probably convince ourselves that this is entire list and remove this
5650  // comment.
5651  assert((isa<LinkageSpecDecl, ExternCContextDecl>(CurDecl)) &&
5652  "Unhandled decl type");
5653  }
5654 
5655  EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, CurDecl->getDeclContext(), NameForLastShim,
5656  Policy);
5657 }
5658 
5659 // Emit the list of shims required for a variable declaration.
5660 // Returns a string containing the FQN of the 'top most' shim, including its
5661 // function call parameters.
5662 static std::string EmitShims(raw_ostream &OS, unsigned &ShimCounter,
5663  PrintingPolicy &Policy, const VarDecl *VD) {
5664  if (!VD->isInAnonymousNamespace())
5665  return "";
5666  std::string RelativeName;
5667  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(RelativeName);
5668  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, Policy, false);
5669  stream.flush();
5670 
5671  EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, VD->getDeclContext(), RelativeName, Policy);
5672  return RelativeName;
5673 }
5674 
5675 bool SYCLIntegrationFooter::emit(raw_ostream &OS) {
5676  PrintingPolicy Policy{S.getLangOpts()};
5677  Policy.adjustForCPlusPlusFwdDecl();
5678  Policy.SuppressTypedefs = true;
5679  Policy.SuppressUnwrittenScope = true;
5680 
5681  llvm::SmallSet<const VarDecl *, 8> Visited;
5682  bool EmittedFirstSpecConstant = false;
5683  bool DeviceGlobalsEmitted = false;
5684  bool HostPipesEmitted = false;
5685 
5686  // Used to uniquely name the 'shim's as we generate the names in each
5687  // anonymous namespace.
5688  unsigned ShimCounter = 0;
5689 
5690  std::string DeviceGlobalsBuf;
5691  llvm::raw_string_ostream DeviceGlobOS(DeviceGlobalsBuf);
5692  std::string HostPipesBuf;
5693  llvm::raw_string_ostream HostPipesOS(HostPipesBuf);
5694  for (const VarDecl *VD : GlobalVars) {
5695  VD = VD->getCanonicalDecl();
5696 
5697  // Skip if this isn't a SpecIdType, DeviceGlobal, or HostPipe. This
5698  // can happen if it was a deduced type.
5699  if (!SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::specialization_id) &&
5700  !SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::host_pipe) &&
5701  !S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
5702  VD->getType()))
5703  continue;
5704 
5705  // Skip if we've already visited this.
5706  if (llvm::find(Visited, VD) != Visited.end())
5707  continue;
5708 
5709  // We only want to emit the #includes if we have a variable that needs
5710  // them, so emit this one on the first time through the loop.
5711  if (!EmittedFirstSpecConstant && !DeviceGlobalsEmitted && !HostPipesEmitted)
5712  OS << "#include <sycl/detail/defines_elementary.hpp>\n";
5713 
5714  Visited.insert(VD);
5715  std::string TopShim = EmitShims(OS, ShimCounter, Policy, VD);
5716  if (S.isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
5717  VD->getType())) {
5718  DeviceGlobalsEmitted = true;
5719  DeviceGlobOS << "device_global_map::add(";
5720  DeviceGlobOS << "(void *)&";
5721  if (VD->isInAnonymousNamespace()) {
5722  DeviceGlobOS << TopShim;
5723  } else {
5724  DeviceGlobOS << "::";
5725  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(DeviceGlobOS, Policy, true);
5726  }
5727  DeviceGlobOS << ", \"";
5728  DeviceGlobOS << SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(),
5729  VD);
5730  DeviceGlobOS << "\");\n";
5731  } else if (SemaSYCL::isSyclType(VD->getType(), SYCLTypeAttr::host_pipe)) {
5732  HostPipesEmitted = true;
5733  HostPipesOS << "host_pipe_map::add(";
5734  HostPipesOS << "(void *)&";
5735  if (VD->isInAnonymousNamespace()) {
5736  HostPipesOS << TopShim;
5737  } else {
5738  HostPipesOS << "::";
5739  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(HostPipesOS, Policy, true);
5740  }
5741  HostPipesOS << ", \"";
5742  HostPipesOS << SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(),
5743  VD);
5744  HostPipesOS << "\");\n";
5745  } else {
5746  EmittedFirstSpecConstant = true;
5747  OS << "namespace sycl {\n";
5748  OS << "inline namespace _V1 {\n";
5749  OS << "namespace detail {\n";
5750  OS << "template<>\n";
5751  OS << "inline const char *get_spec_constant_symbolic_ID_impl<";
5752 
5753  if (VD->isInAnonymousNamespace()) {
5754  OS << TopShim;
5755  } else {
5756  OS << "::";
5757  VD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, Policy, true);
5758  }
5759 
5760  OS << ">() {\n";
5761  OS << " return \"";
5762  OS << SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::ComputeName(S.getASTContext(), VD);
5763  OS << "\";\n";
5764  OS << "}\n";
5765  OS << "} // namespace detail\n";
5766  OS << "} // namespace _V1\n";
5767  OS << "} // namespace sycl\n";
5768  }
5769  }
5770 
5771  if (EmittedFirstSpecConstant)
5772  OS << "#include <sycl/detail/spec_const_integration.hpp>\n";
5773 
5774  if (DeviceGlobalsEmitted) {
5775  OS << "#include <sycl/detail/device_global_map.hpp>\n";
5776  DeviceGlobOS.flush();
5777  OS << "namespace sycl::detail {\n";
5778  OS << "namespace {\n";
5779  OS << "__sycl_device_global_registration::__sycl_device_global_"
5780  "registration() noexcept {\n";
5781  OS << DeviceGlobalsBuf;
5782  OS << "}\n";
5783  OS << "} // namespace (unnamed)\n";
5784  OS << "} // namespace sycl::detail\n";
5785 
5786  S.getSyclIntegrationHeader().addDeviceGlobalRegistration();
5787  }
5788 
5789  if (HostPipesEmitted) {
5790  OS << "#include <sycl/detail/host_pipe_map.hpp>\n";
5791  HostPipesOS.flush();
5792  OS << "namespace sycl::detail {\n";
5793  OS << "namespace {\n";
5794  OS << "__sycl_host_pipe_registration::__sycl_host_pipe_"
5795  "registration() noexcept {\n";
5796  OS << HostPipesBuf;
5797  OS << "}\n";
5798  OS << "} // namespace (unnamed)\n";
5799  OS << "} // namespace sycl::detail\n";
5800 
5801  S.getSyclIntegrationHeader().addHostPipeRegistration();
5802  }
5803 
5804  return true;
5805 }
5806 
5807 ExprResult SemaSYCL::BuildUniqueStableIdExpr(SourceLocation OpLoc,
5808  SourceLocation LParen,
5809  SourceLocation RParen, Expr *E) {
5810  if (!E->isInstantiationDependent()) {
5811  // Special handling to get us better error messages for a member variable.
5812  if (auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E->IgnoreUnlessSpelledInSource())) {
5813  if (isa<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl()))
5814  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_unique_stable_id_global_storage);
5815  else
5816  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_unique_stable_id_expected_var);
5817  return ExprError();
5818  }
5819 
5820  auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreUnlessSpelledInSource());
5821 
5822  if (!DRE || !isa_and_nonnull<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
5823  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_unique_stable_id_expected_var);
5824  return ExprError();
5825  }
5826 
5827  auto *Var = cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
5828 
5829  if (!Var->hasGlobalStorage()) {
5830  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_unique_stable_id_global_storage);
5831  return ExprError();
5832  }
5833  }
5834 
5835  return SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr::Create(getASTContext(), OpLoc, LParen, RParen,
5836  E);
5837 }
5838 
5839 ExprResult SemaSYCL::ActOnUniqueStableIdExpr(SourceLocation OpLoc,
5840  SourceLocation LParen,
5841  SourceLocation RParen, Expr *E) {
5842  return BuildUniqueStableIdExpr(OpLoc, LParen, RParen, E);
5843 }
5844 
5845 ExprResult SemaSYCL::BuildUniqueStableNameExpr(SourceLocation OpLoc,
5846  SourceLocation LParen,
5847  SourceLocation RParen,
5848  TypeSourceInfo *TSI) {
5849  return SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr::Create(getASTContext(), OpLoc, LParen,
5850  RParen, TSI);
5851 }
5852 
5853 ExprResult SemaSYCL::ActOnUniqueStableNameExpr(SourceLocation OpLoc,
5854  SourceLocation LParen,
5855  SourceLocation RParen,
5856  ParsedType ParsedTy) {
5857  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = nullptr;
5858  QualType Ty = SemaRef.GetTypeFromParser(ParsedTy, &TSI);
5859 
5860  if (Ty.isNull())
5861  return ExprError();
5862  if (!TSI)
5863  TSI = getASTContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty, LParen);
5864 
5865  return BuildUniqueStableNameExpr(OpLoc, LParen, RParen, TSI);
5866 }
